('OIL_OF_MENDING', 'consumables', 'Oil of Mending', '3', NULL, '9', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A vial of <i>oil of mending</i> appears to have countless translucent threads swirling within. Applying this oil to an item casts a 2nd-level <i>mending</i> spell to repair the item.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=178'),
('ALIGNED_OIL', 'consumables', 'Aligned Oil', '9', NULL, '140', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This oil fills a weapon with cosmic power of an alignment. Each <i>aligned oil</i> is crafted to one alignment: chaos, evil, good, or law (such as a <i>good-aligned oil</i>). A weapon anointed with this oil gains the effects of the property rune matching its alignment: 
<treasure%291%%>
 <i>anarchic</i> (chaos), 
 <treasure%292%%>
  <i>axiomatic</i> (law), 
  <treasure%300%%>
   <i>holy</i> (good), or 
   <treasure%308%%>
    <i>unholy</i> (evil). This lasts for 1 minute.
    <br>
    <br>
    <b>Activate</b>  Interact
   </treasure%308%%>
  </treasure%300%%>
 </treasure%292%%>
</treasure%291%%>', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=173'),
('ANTIMAGIC_OIL', 'consumables', 'Antimagic Oil', '20', NULL, '13000', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This oil contains energy that repels nearly all types of magic. When you apply this oil to armor, the creature wearing the armor becomes immune to all spells, effects of magic items (the wearer’s and those of others), and effects with the magical trait for 1 minute. The oil affects neither the magic of the armor nor the fundamental runes of weapons attacking the wearer. Magical effects from a source of 20th level or higher, such as a deity, still function on the armor’s wearer.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=172'),
('OIL_OF_POTENCY', 'consumables', 'Oil of Potency', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When you apply this thick, viscous oil to a non-magical weapon or suit of armor, that item immediately becomes magically potent. If the item is a weapon, it temporarily becomes a <i>+1 striking weapon</i>, or, if it’s armor, it temporarily becomes <i>+1 resilient armor</i>. This lasts for 1 minute.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=179'),
('HEALING_POTION_MODERATE)', 'consumables', 'Healing Potion (Moderate)', '6', NULL, '50', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A healing potion is a vial of a ruby-red liquid that imparts a tingling sensation as the drinker’s wounds heal rapidly. When you drink a healing potion, you regain the listed number of Hit Points.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Minor) Item 1</b><br><b>Level</b> 1; <b>Price</b> 4 gp<br>The potion restores 1d8 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Lesser) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>The potion restores 2d8+5 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Moderate) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 50 gp<br>The potion restores 3d8+10 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 400 gp<br>The potion restores 6d8+20 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Major) Item 18</b><br><b>Level</b> 18; <b>Price</b> 5,000 gp<br>The potion restores 8d8+30 Hit Points.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=186'),
('POTION_OF_QUICKNESS', 'consumables', 'Potion of Quickness', '8', NULL, '90', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Drinking this silver potion grants you the effects of <i>haste</i> for 1 minute.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=191'),
('HEALING_POTION_MAJOR)', 'consumables', 'Healing Potion (Major)', '18', NULL, '5000', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A healing potion is a vial of a ruby-red liquid that imparts a tingling sensation as the drinker’s wounds heal rapidly. When you drink a healing potion, you regain the listed number of Hit Points.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Minor) Item 1</b><br><b>Level</b> 1; <b>Price</b> 4 gp<br>The potion restores 1d8 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Lesser) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>The potion restores 2d8+5 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Moderate) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 50 gp<br>The potion restores 3d8+10 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 400 gp<br>The potion restores 6d8+20 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Major) Item 18</b><br><b>Level</b> 18; <b>Price</b> 5,000 gp<br>The potion restores 8d8+30 Hit Points.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=186'),
('OIL_OF_KEEN_EDGES', 'consumables', 'Oil of Keen Edges', '11', NULL, '250', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When this silvery salve is applied to a melee weapon that deals piercing or slashing damage, the weapon grows sharper and more dangerous for 1 minute, granting it the benefits of the <i>keen</i>&nbsp;rune. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=177'),
('HEALING_POTION_LESSER)', 'consumables', 'Healing Potion (Lesser)', '3', NULL, '12', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A healing potion is a vial of a ruby-red liquid that imparts a tingling sensation as the drinker’s wounds heal rapidly. When you drink a healing potion, you regain the listed number of Hit Points.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Minor) Item 1</b><br><b>Level</b> 1; <b>Price</b> 4 gp<br>The potion restores 1d8 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Lesser) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>The potion restores 2d8+5 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Moderate) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 50 gp<br>The potion restores 3d8+10 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 400 gp<br>The potion restores 6d8+20 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Major) Item 18</b><br><b>Level</b> 18; <b>Price</b> 5,000 gp<br>The potion restores 8d8+30 Hit Points.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=186'),
('POTION_OF_RESISTANCE_LESSER)', 'consumables', 'Potion of Resistance (Lesser)', '6', NULL, '45', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Drinking this thick, fortifying potion grants resistance against a single damage type for 1 hour. Each <i>potion of resistance</i> is created to defend against acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic damage (and is called a <i>lesser potion of fire resistance</i> or the like).<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Potion of Resistance (Lesser) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 45 gp<br>You gain resistance 5 to the appropriate energy type.<br><br><b>Potion of Resistance (Moderate) Item 10</b><br><b>Level</b> 10; <b>Price</b> 180 gp<br>You gain resistance 10 to the appropriate energy type.<br><br><b>Potion of Resistance (Greater) Item 14</b><br><b>Level</b> 14; <b>Price</b> 850 gp<br>You gain resistance 15 to the appropriate energy type.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=192'),
('OBFUSCATION_OIL', 'consumables', 'Obfuscation Oil', '15', NULL, '1200', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can spread this blue-gray gel on a single item with a Bulk of 3 or less to ward it against magical detection. It becomes immune to divination magic of 8th level or lower (such as <i>locate</i>). This oil is permanent, but it can be removed with acid. Removing the oil in this way usually takes 1 minute for objects with Bulk of 1 or less, or a number of minutes equal to the item’s Bulk.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=175'),
('TRUTH_POTION', 'consumables', 'Truth Potion', '6', NULL, '46', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'For 10 minutes after drinking this astringent potion, you can’t intentionally lie and may be compelled to tell the truth. Upon drinking the potion, attempt a DC 19 Will save. You can voluntarily fail or critically fail.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Success</b> The potion does not affect you.<br><b>Failure</b> When you speak, you must tell the truth.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> As failure, and when someone asks you a question, you must attempt another DC 19 Will saving throw. If you fail this saving throw, you must answer the question truthfully if you are able to do so; if you succeed, you are temporarily immune to further attempts to ask the same question within the potion’s duration.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=200'),
('POTION_OF_WATER_BREATHING', 'consumables', 'Potion of Water Breathing', '3', NULL, '11', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This filmy, gray potion smells of an old fish midden and tastes even worse. After drinking this potion, you gain the effects of a 2nd-level <i>water breathing</i> spell for 1 hour. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=196'),
('DRAGON_S_BREATH_POTION_ADULT)', 'consumables', 'Dragon''s Breath Potion (Adult)', '12', NULL, '400', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This liquid contains blood from a certain type of dragon. For 1 hour after you imbibe the concoction, you can unleash a breath weapon used by that type of dragon. The potency of the breath depends on the potion’s type, based on the age of the dragon whose blood was used to make the potion. This potion has the trait matching the damage type of the breath weapon<br><br>. Exhaling dragon breath uses a single action. The damage type and the area of the dragon breath depend on the type of dragon blood in the potion, as shown in the table below. Regardless of the dragon type, the breath weapon deals 4d6 damage, and each creature in the area must attempt a DC 23 basic save of a type determined by the type of the dragon. After you use the breath weapon, you can’t do so again for 1d4 rounds.<h2>Dragon''s Breath Potion</b>
