('HEALING_POTION_GREATER)', 'consumables', 'Healing Potion (Greater)', '12', NULL, '400', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A healing potion is a vial of a ruby-red liquid that imparts a tingling sensation as the drinker’s wounds heal rapidly. When you drink a healing potion, you regain the listed number of Hit Points.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Minor) Item 1</b><br><b>Level</b> 1; <b>Price</b> 4 gp<br>The potion restores 1d8 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Lesser) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>The potion restores 2d8+5 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Moderate) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 50 gp<br>The potion restores 3d8+10 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 400 gp<br>The potion restores 6d8+20 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Major) Item 18</b><br><b>Level</b> 18; <b>Price</b> 5,000 gp<br>The potion restores 8d8+30 Hit Points.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=186'),
('OIL_OF_ANIMATION', 'consumables', 'Oil of Animation', '12', NULL, '330', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can rub this bronze-colored oil onto a melee weapon to grant it the benefits of the <i>dancing</i> rune. Once you fail a flat check for the weapon, causing it to fall, this effect ends.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=176'),
('POTION_OF_LEAPING', 'consumables', 'Potion of Leaping', '5', NULL, '21', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'For 1 minute after you drink this fizzy potion, whenever you Leap, you gain the effect of the 1st-level <i>jump</i> spell.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=190'),
('POTION_OF_SWIMMING_MODERATE)', 'consumables', 'Potion of Swimming (Moderate)', '6', NULL, '50', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This potion tastes like salt water, and sandy grit settles to the bottom of its container. When you drink it, you gain a swim Speed equal to your land Speed for 10 minutes.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Potion of Swimming (Moderate) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 50 gp<br><br><b>Potion of Swimming (Greater) Item 11</b><br><b>Level</b> 11; <b>Price</b> 250 gp<br>The swim Speed lasts for 1 hour.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=193'),
('POTION_OF_FLYING_GREATER)', 'consumables', 'Potion of Flying (Greater)', '15', NULL, '1000', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Upon drinking this effervescent concoction, you gain a fly Speed of 40 feet for 1 minute.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Potion of Flying Item 8</b><br><b>Level</b> 8; <b>Price</b> 100 gp<br><br><b>Potion of Flying (Greater) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 1,000 gp<br>The fly Speed lasts for 1 hour.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=189'),
('POTION_OF_UNDETECTABILITY', 'consumables', 'Potion of Undetectability', '18', NULL, '4400', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Drinking this dull-black liquid makes you undetectable to divinations. This grants the same effects as <i>mind blank</i>, but without the bonus against mental effects. You also gain the effects of a 4th-level <i>invisibility</i> spell, which protects against <i>see invisibility</i> spells of 8th level and lower and has a DC of 36 against <i>true seeing</i>. The potion’s effects last for 10 minutes. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=195'),
('SALVE_OF_ANTIPARALYSIS_GREATER)', 'consumables', 'Salve of Antiparalysis (Greater)', '12', NULL, '325', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Applying this filmy salve to a creature helps it overcome magical paralysis. The creature recovers as if it were the target of a 3rd-level <i>remove paralysis</i> spell. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Salve of Antiparalysis Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 40 gp<br><br><b>Salve of Antiparalysis (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 325 gp<br>A <i>greater salve of antiparalysis can potentially remove petrification. The creature recovers as if it were the target of both a 6th-level <i>remove paralysis spell and a <i>stone to flesh spell.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=182'),
('POTION_OF_RESISTANCE_MODERATE)', 'consumables', 'Potion of Resistance (Moderate)', '10', NULL, '180', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Drinking this thick, fortifying potion grants resistance against a single damage type for 1 hour. Each <i>potion of resistance</i> is created to defend against acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic damage (and is called a <i>lesser potion of fire resistance</i> or the like).<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Potion of Resistance (Lesser) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 45 gp<br>You gain resistance 5 to the appropriate energy type.<br><br><b>Potion of Resistance (Moderate) Item 10</b><br><b>Level</b> 10; <b>Price</b> 180 gp<br>You gain resistance 10 to the appropriate energy type.<br><br><b>Potion of Resistance (Greater) Item 14</b><br><b>Level</b> 14; <b>Price</b> 850 gp<br>You gain resistance 15 to the appropriate energy type.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=192'),
('SALVE_OF_SLIPPERINESS', 'consumables', 'Salve of Slipperiness', '5', NULL, '25', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This greenish, persistent grease can be applied to armor to make it extremely slippery for 8 hours, granting the wearer a +2 item bonus to Acrobatics checks to Escape or to Squeeze.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=183'),
('HEALING_POTION_MINOR)', 'consumables', 'Healing Potion (Minor)', '1', NULL, '4', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A healing potion is a vial of a ruby-red liquid that imparts a tingling sensation as the drinker’s wounds heal rapidly. When you drink a healing potion, you regain the listed number of Hit Points.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Minor) Item 1</b><br><b>Level</b> 1; <b>Price</b> 4 gp<br>The potion restores 1d8 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Lesser) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>The potion restores 2d8+5 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Moderate) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 50 gp<br>The potion restores 3d8+10 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 400 gp<br>The potion restores 6d8+20 Hit Points.<br><br><b>Healing Potion (Major) Item 18</b><br><b>Level</b> 18; <b>Price</b> 5,000 gp<br>The potion restores 8d8+30 Hit Points.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=186'),
('SHRINKING_POTION_GREATER)', 'consumables', 'Shrinking Potion (Greater)', '8', NULL, '90', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This fungus-flavored potion conveys the effects of the <i>shrink</i> spell to make you and all your gear smaller. After the onset, you remain small for 10 minutes. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Shrinking Potion Item 4</b><br><b>Level</b> 4; <b>Price</b> 15 gp<br><br><b>Shrinking Potion (Greater) Item 8</b><br><b>Level</b> 8; <b>Price</b> 90 gp<br>This potion has no onset, lasts for 1 hour, and grants the effects of a 4th-level <i>shrink spell. In addition, you gain a +2 item bonus to Stealth checks while shrunken.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=197'),
('SALVE_OF_ANTIPARALYSIS', 'consumables', 'Salve of Antiparalysis', '6', NULL, '40', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Applying this filmy salve to a creature helps it overcome magical paralysis. The creature recovers as if it were the target of a 3rd-level <i>remove paralysis</i> spell. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Salve of Antiparalysis Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 40 gp<br><br><b>Salve of Antiparalysis (Greater) Item 12</b><br><b>Level</b> 12; <b>Price</b> 325 gp<br>A <i>greater salve of antiparalysis can potentially remove petrification. The creature recovers as if it were the target of both a 6th-level <i>remove paralysis spell and a <i>stone to flesh spell.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=182'),
('POTION_OF_TONGUES', 'consumables', 'Potion of Tongues', '12', NULL, '320', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This sour potion enlivens your tongue with unusual flavors and uncommon eloquence, allowing you to speak and understand all languages for 4 hours after you drink it. This doesn’t allow you to read these languages in their written form.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=194'),
('OIL_OF_REPULSION', 'consumables', 'Oil of Repulsion', '11', NULL, '175', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This oil contains magnetically charged iron filings repelled into opposite ends of the vial. For 1 minute after you apply this oil to armor, any creature that hits you with a melee Strike must attempt a DC 28 Fortitude save with the following effects.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Success</b> The creature is unaffected.<br><b>Failure</b> The creature is pushed up to 10 feet away from you (the GM determines the direction).<br><b>Critical Failure</b> As failure, and the creature is also knocked prone.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=180'),
('OIL_OF_WEIGHTLESSNESS_GREATER)', 'consumables', 'Oil of Weightlessness (Greater)', '6', NULL, '36', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 2 hands', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can spread this shimmering oil on an item of 1 Bulk or less to make it feel weightless. It has negligible Bulk for 1 hour.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Oil of Weightlessness Item 2</b><br><b>Level</b> 2; <b>Price</b> 6 gp<br><br><b>Oil of Weightlessness (Greater) Item 6</b><br><b>Level</b> 6; <b>Price</b> 36 gp<br>This oil can affect an item of 2 Bulk or less and lasts 8 hours.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=181'),
('TRUESIGHT_POTION', 'consumables', 'Truesight Potion', '16', NULL, '1500', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Upon drinking this clear, refreshing potion, you can see things as they actually are. You gain the benefits of a 7th-level <i>true seeing</i> spell that has a counteract modifier of +25.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=199'),
('GALLOWS_TOOTH', 'consumables', 'Gallows Tooth', '8', NULL, '100', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This grisly molar hangs from a cord threaded through a tiny hole just above its dried, exposed root. When you activate this talisman, the creature you’re attacking becomes flat-footed until the end of the current turn.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Interact; <b>Trigger</b> You attack an adjacent creature and havne''t rolled your attack roll; <b>Requirements</b> You''re a master in Intimidation', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=214'),
('VIPER_S_FANG', 'consumables', 'Viper''s Fang', '14', NULL, '850', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When you activate this resin-strengthened viper skull, you make an Attack of Opportunity <br><b>Trigger</b> A creature within your reach uses a manipulate action or a move action, makes a ranged attack, or leaves a square during a move action it’s using.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=238'),
('POTENCY_CRYSTAL', 'consumables', 'Potency Crystal', '1', NULL, '4', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This fluorite crystal glows with a strange phosphorescence. When you activate the crystal, the weapon becomes a <i>+1 striking weapon</i> for the rest of the turn, gaining a +1 item bonus to the attack roll and increasing the damage on a hit to two weapon damage dice.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You make an attack with the affixed weapon, but you haven''t rolled yet', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=231'),
('VANISHING_COIN', 'consumables', 'Vanishing Coin', '10', NULL, '160', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This copper coin dangles from a leather strip strung through a hole drilled in the center. Until activated, the coin becomes invisible for a few seconds at random intervals every few minutes. When you activate the coin, it casts a 2nd-level <i>invisibility</i> spell on you, lasting until the end of your next turn.<br><br><b>Activate</b> free action  Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt a Stealth check for initiative, but you haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master in Stealth', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=237'),
('OWLBEAR_CLAW', 'consumables', 'Owlbear Claw', '1', NULL, '3', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This claw set in an iron clasp and chain isn’t always the claw of an owlbear. When you activate the claw, the triggering attack gains the weapon’s critical specialization effect. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You critically succeed at an attack roll with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=230'),
('GRIM_TROPHY', 'consumables', 'Grim Trophy', '7', NULL, '55', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This talisman comes in many forms, most often a severed piece of a humanoid creature displayed in some gruesome manner. When you activate the trophy, select two targets and compare your Intimidation check result to both of their DCs. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt an Intimidation check to Coerce or Demoralize, but you haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You are an expert in Initimidation', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=216'),
('MURDERER_S_KNOT', 'consumables', 'Murderer''s Knot', '7', NULL, '66', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This black strand of leather is tied to look like a peace knot when the weapon is stowed, but it doesn’t hamper drawing the weapon. When you activate the knot, the creature you damaged takes 1d6 persistent bleed damage.<br><br> If you have the Twist the Knife feat, the talisman instead deals persistent bleed damage equal to your sneak attack damage.<br><br><b>Activate</b> free action Command; <b>Trigger</b> You damage a flat-footed creature with a Strike using the Affixed weapon; <b>Requirements</b> You are an expert with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=228'),
('BLOODSEEKER_BEAK', 'consumables', 'Bloodseeker Beak', '4', NULL, '20', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This long, hollow proboscis is harvested from the notorious bloodseeker beast and drips a trickle of blood. When you activate the beak, you deal an extra 1d4 precision damage on your damage roll. If you deal sneak attack damage to the creature, you also deal 1d4 persistent bleed damage.<br><br><b>Activate</b  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You hit a flat-footed creature with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=201'),
('FEATHER_STEP_STONE', 'consumables', 'Feather Step Stone', '3', NULL, '8', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This stone, usually shaped as a cabochon, is a small chunk of amber with a bit of feather or a flying insect caught within it. When you activate the stone, you ignore the effects of any difficult terrain and greater difficult terrain you move through until the end of your turn.<br><br><b>Activate</b> free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You Stride or Step; <b>Requirements</b> You are an expert in Acrobatics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=212'),
('CRYING_ANGEL_PENDANT', 'consumables', 'Crying Angel Pendant', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When you activate this alabaster pendant, your critical failure becomes a normal failure instead.<br><br><b>Activate</b> free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You critically fail to Administer First Aid; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Medicine', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=203'),
('MUMMIFIED_BAT', 'consumables', 'Mummified Bat', '10', NULL, '175', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This talisman is the magically treated corpse of a tiny bat bound in papyrus. When you activate the bat, the affixed weapon detects vibrations around you and guides your perception. You gain the benefits of the fighter Blind-Fight class feat for 1 minute.<br><br> If you have the Blind-Fight feat, you gain imprecise echolocation with a range of 30 feet for 1 minute. This makes creatures that would be undetected by you because you can’t see them hidden instead.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Command; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master in Perception', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=227'),
('MONKEY_PIN', 'consumables', 'Monkey Pin', '2', NULL, '6', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small brass pin is in the shape of a monkey climbing a tree. When you activate this talisman, use a Climb action. If you succeed, you move your full Speed during the Climb. If you roll a critical failure, you get a failure instead.<br><br><b>Activate</b> 1 action Climb; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Athletics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=226'),
('MENDING_LATTICE', 'consumables', 'Mending Lattice', '13', NULL, '525', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a shield or weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This lattice of reinforced iron is shaped into a perfect octagon. When you activate it, it negates the damage and instantly and completely repairs the affixed item.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Command; <b>Trigger</b> The affixed item would take damage; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master in Crafting', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=224'),
('JADE_BAUBLE', 'consumables', 'Jade Bauble', '8', NULL, '100', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a melee weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This bit of jade is usually carved in the shape of a duelist, or sometimes a multi-armed creature. When you activate the bauble, it magically draws the attention of foes. Until the start of your next turn, enemies within the reach of the weapon the talisman is affixed to are flat-footed.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Command; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=222'),
('FEAR_GEM', 'consumables', 'Fear Gem', '4', NULL, '20', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Dark smoke seems to writhe within this obsidian gem. When you activate the gem, you make an Intimidating Strike, as the fighter feat.<br><br> If you have the Intimidating Strike feat, increase the frightened condition value from this Intimidating Strike to frightened 2, or frightened 3 on a critical hit.<br><br><b>Activate</b> 2 actions Intimidating Strike', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=211'),
('ONYX_PANTHER', 'consumables', 'Onyx Panther', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small stone is a stylized panther shape. When you activate it, you can move your full Speed (instead of half) during the triggering Sneak and any other time you Sneak this turn.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You use a Sneak action; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Stealth', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=229'),
('IRON_CUDGEL', 'consumables', 'Iron Cudgel', '14', NULL, '900', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This miniature iron cudgel is typically affixed to a weapon by an iron chain. When you activate the cudgel, you use Brutal Finish, as the fighter feat. You must meet the normal requirements, including those of the press trait.<br><br> If you have the Brutal Finish feat, add two additional weapon damage dice on a success or a failure.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Brutal Finish; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=219'),
('DISPELLING_SLIVER', 'consumables', 'Dispelling Sliver', '17', NULL, '2400', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Made from a treated sliver of cold iron, this talisman allows you to counteract magical effects. When you activate the <i>dispelling sliver</i>, it attempts to counteract a single spell active on the target, with the effects of an 8th-level <i>dispel magic</i> spell. (counteract modifier
+29)<br><br> If you activate the talisman on a successful Dispelling Slice, the talisman attempts to counteract all spells active on the target.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> Your Strike damages a target; <b>Requirements</b> You''re a master with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=205'),
('FLAME_NAVETTE', 'consumables', 'Flame Navette', '16', NULL, '1800', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This piece of bronzite is shaped like an oval with points at both ends. It has a carved flame at its center and is traditionally worn over the heart. You can activate only one <i>flame navette</i> per day. When you activate the navette, you gain the benefit of the fighter’s Determination class feat, with a counteract modifier of +22. If you have the Determination feat, you can use your own modifier if it’s better.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Envision; <b>Requirements</b> You''re an Expert in Will saves', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=213'),
('HUNTER_S_BANE', 'consumables', 'Hunter''s Bane', '2', NULL, '6', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This talisman is a ring of dried, interwoven leaves. When you activate the <i>hunter’s bane</i>, you sense the exact location of the attacker, making it hidden from you instead of undetected. If the attacker is behind lead, the <i>hunter’s bane</i> fails and is wasted.<br><br><b>Activate</b> free action  Envision; <b>Trigger</b> An undetected enemy hits you with an attack; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Survival', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=217'),
('TIGER_MENUKI', 'consumables', 'Tiger Menuki', '5', NULL, '30', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This tiger formed of pewter snarls viciously from your weapon’s grip. When you activate the tiger, the affixed weapon gains the sweep trait for the triggering attack and all other attacks for 1 minute.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You Strike with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=236'),
('EMERALD_GRASSHOPPER', 'consumables', 'Emerald Grasshopper', '5', NULL, '30', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This metal grasshopper studded with emeralds is usually clasped to the legs of a suit of armor. When you activate it, if you succeed at the Athletics check, you Leap up to 50 feet vertically and up to 10 feet horizontally. If you critically succeed, you can Leap up to 75 feet vertically and 20 feet horizontally. If you don’t end your jump on solid ground, you flutter in the air until the end of your turn, then fall harmlessly at a rate of 60 feet per round until you reach the ground.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt a High Jump but haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You''re an expert in Acrobatics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=208'),
('FADE_BAND', 'consumables', 'Fade Band', '12', NULL, '320', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This thin, silvery wire wraps around your armor. When you activate the band, it casts a 2nd-level <i>invisibility</i> spell on you.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> An attach misses you; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master in Stealth', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=210'),
('SHARK_TOOTH_CHARM', 'consumables', 'Shark Tooth Charm', '5', NULL, '23', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This dried seaweed bracelet is lined with charms shaped like small shark teeth. When you activate the bracelet, if you roll a success on the triggering check, you get a critical success instead (if you roll a critical failure, you get a failure instead). If you fail the Acrobatics check against a grabbing creature, the creature must either release you as a free action or take 2d8 piercing damage as shark’s teeth momentarily emerge from your skin. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Command; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt to Escape using Acrobatics for your roll, but you haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You are an expert in Acrobatics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=233'),
('IRON_MEDALLION', 'consumables', 'Iron Medallion', '10', NULL, '175', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small medallion is shaped like a shield. When you activate it, you gain a +2 status bonus to saves against fear for 1 minute. On the triggering save, if the outcome of your roll is a failure, you get a success instead or if the outcome is a critical failure, you get a failure instead. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt a Will save against a fear effect but haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You have master proficiency in Will saves or have the bravery class feature', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=221'),
('EFFERVESCENT_AMPOULE', 'consumables', 'Effervescent Ampoule', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Light spring water fizzes and bubbles within this small glass globe, spilling onto the affixed armor when activated. Until the end of your turn, the armor lets you move across water and other liquids as if they were solid ground. If you Stride or Step over a weight-sensitive pressure plate, you don’t cause the plate to depress, which prevents you from triggering any device or hazard attached to the pressure plate. When the ampoule’s effect ends, you sink, fall, break through flimsy ground, or land on pressure plates as normal for your current location.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Requirements</b> You''re an expert in Acrobatics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=207'),
('EYE_OF_APPREHENSION', 'consumables', 'Eye of Apprehension', '12', NULL, '400', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This round piece of cymophane’s silky inclusion makes it look like a cat’s eye. While affixed, it makes you jittery. When you activate it, roll Perception twice and use the higher result.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You are about to roll Perception for initiative but haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master in Perception', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=209'),
('BRONZE_BULL_PENDANT', 'consumables', 'Bronze Bull Pendant', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This pendant is forged from grainy steel and depicts a snorting bull’s face. The pendant must be attached to the chest area or on a shoulder guard. When you activate the pendant, you gain a +2 status bonus to the Athletics check to Shove, and if you roll a critical failure on the check, you get a failure instead.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt an Athletics check to Shove, but you haven''t rolled yet; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Athletics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=202'),
('IRON_EQUALIZER', 'consumables', 'Iron Equalizer', '12', NULL, '400', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small iron band has a shifting weight that helps equalize the affixed weapon’s balance. When you activate it, you use Certain Strike, as the fighter feat. You must meet the normal requirements, including those of the press trait.<br><br> If you have the Certain Strike feat, the failure effect increases to deal the weapon’s normal damage.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Certain Strike; <b>Requirements</b> You are a master with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=220'),
('GHOST_DUST', 'consumables', 'Ghost Dust', '16', NULL, '1800', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small vial is filled with a grayish-green dust rendered from dried ectoplasm. When you activate the dust, it casts a 4th-level <i>invisibility</i> spell on you. This comes into effect before you move during the triggering action.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You use an action with the move trait; <b>Requirements</b> You are legendary in Stealth', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=215'),
('WOLF_FANG', 'consumables', 'Wolf Fang', '1', NULL, '4', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This wolf canine is bound in a strip of leather and tied to a buckle or strap of a suit of armor. When you activate the fang, you deal bludgeoning damage equal to your Strength modifier to the target of your Trip. If your Trip would already deal physical damage that doesn’t include an ability modifier, add your Strength modifier to that damage.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You successfully Trip a foe; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Athletics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=239'),
('DAZING_COIL', 'consumables', 'Dazing Coil', '14', NULL, '900', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This knot of copper wire reshapes itself in a new pattern every time its affixed weapon deals damage. When you activate the coil, the damaged creature must succeed at a DC 31 Will save or be stunned 1. If it critically fails, it instead becomes stunned 2.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You deal damage to a flat-footed creature with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=204'),
('JADE_CAT', 'consumables', 'Jade Cat', '2', NULL, '6', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A thumb-sized feline carved of rare stone, the <i>jade cat</i> is typically worn as a pendant upon a suit of armor. For 1 minute after you activate the cat, you treat all falls as 20 feet shorter, you are not flat-footed when you Balance, and narrow surfaces and uneven ground are not difficult terrain for you.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Command; <b>Trigger</b> You fall or attempt an Acrobatics check to Balance; <b>Requirements</b> You are trained in Acrobatics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=223'),
('MEZMERIZING_OPAL', 'consumables', 'Mezmerizing Opal', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This silver-bound opal pendant is afire with iridescence. When you activate it, if the outcome of your triggering Deception check is a critical failure, you get a failure instead (or if the outcome is a success, you get a critical success instead).<br><br><b>Activate</b> free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt a Deception check to Feint, but you haven''t rolled yet', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=225'),
('IRON_CUBE', 'consumables', 'Iron Cube', '6', NULL, '50', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This cube of blackened iron is affixed to a weapon with an iron chain. When you activate the cube, you use Knockdown, as the fighter feat.<br><br> If you have the Knockdown feat, ignore its normal size restrictions.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  2 actions Knockdown; <b>Requirements</b> You are an expert with the affixed weapon', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=218'),
('SAVIOR_SPIKE', 'consumables', 'Savior Spike', '2', NULL, '7', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This pyramid-shaped spike is attached to an armor’s chest piece. When you activate the spike, it shoots a strand of force to help you gain purchase. If you roll a success on the triggering attempt, you get a critical success instead (if you roll a critical failure, you get a failure instead). <br><br><b>Activate</b> free action  Command; <b>Trigger</b> You attempt to Grab an Edge but haven''t rolled; <b>Requirements</b> You''re an expert in Reflex', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=232'),
('SWIFT_BLOCK_CABOCHON', 'consumables', 'Swift Block Cabochon', '7', NULL, '70', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to a shield', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This clear quartz cabochon attaches to the center of your shield. When you activate the cabochon, you use the Shield Block reaction even if you hadn’t raised the affixed shield (and even if you don’t normally have that reaction).<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Trigger</b> You take damage from a physical attack while you don''t have the affixed shield raised', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=235'),
('SNEAKY_KEY', 'consumables', 'Sneaky Key', '5', NULL, '22', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small silver skeleton key can be pinned to armor or a sleeve. When you turn the key to activate it, for the next minute, if the outcome of any your attempts to Pick a Lock is a critical failure, you get a failure instead.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Interact; <b>Requirements</b> You are an expert in Thievery', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=234'),
('DRAGON_TURTLE_SCALE', 'consumables', 'Dragon Turtle Scale', '4', NULL, '13', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This shimmering green scale is usually attached to a golden clasp or chain. When you activate the scale, for 1 minute you gain a swim Speed equal to half your land Speed.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action Envision; <b>Requirements</b> You''re an expert in Athletics', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=206'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_CHEST)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Chest)', '3', '1', '10', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When you use this token, a small wooden chest appears and immediately opens. This chest can hold up to 10 Bulk worth of items. Once the chest is closed, it transforms again—this time into a key—taking all of the stored items with it. You can activate this key by spending an Interact action to turn it in an imaginary lock, which causes it to transform back into a chest with all of the items still inside. Once it has turned into a chest a second time, it forever remains a wooden chest.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('UNHOLY_WATER', 'consumables', 'Unholy Water', '1', '1', '3', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'An evil deity’s malice lies within this vial of water. You activate a vial of <i>unholy water</i> by throwing it as a Strike. It’s a simple thrown weapon with a range increment of 20 feet. Unlike an alchemical bomb, it doesn’t add the manipulate trait to the attack made with it.<br><br> <i>Unholy water</i> deals 1d6 evil damage and 1 evil splash damage. It damages only celestials and creatures that have a weakness to evil damage. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Strike', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=248'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_LADDER)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Ladder)', '1', '1', '3', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When activated, this feather transforms permanently into a 20-foot-long wooden ladder.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_FAN)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Fan)', '4', '1', '15', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Activating this feather requires you to fan it in a given direction. If this direction is toward the sail of a vessel, the feather flutters up toward the sail and fans continuously, filling the sail with air and granting the vessel a +10-foot circumstance bonus to its Speed for 8 hours. If fanned in any other direction, it instead produces a single casting of gust of wind (DC 20).', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('JAVELIN_OF_LIGHTNING', 'consumables', 'Javelin of Lightning', '9', '2', '110', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This item looks like a normal javelin carved with lightning-bolt motifs. If thrown without being activated, it wobbles in the air and fails to strike true. When you Activate the javelin, your command makes the carvings crackle with electricity. You then hurl the javelin. It shatters immediately after leaving your hand and unleashes its magic as a 4th-level <i>lightning bolt</i> originating from your space. The bolt deals 5d12 electricity damage and has a Reflex save DC of 25.<br><br><b>Activate</b> 2 actions Command, Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=246'),
('ELEMENTAL_GEM', 'consumables', 'Elemental Gem', '10', '2', '200', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You shout the name of an elemental lord and dash this glassy gem against a hard surface to activate it. It cracks open, casting a 5th-level <i>summon elemental</i> spell to summon forth an elemental you control as long as you spend an action each round to Sustain the Activation. <br><br> This gem comes in four varieties: transparent for a living whirlwind, light brown for a living landslide, reddish orange for a living wildfire, and blue-green for a living waterfall.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  2 actions Command, Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=243'),
('DUST_OF_DISAPPEARANCE', 'consumables', 'Dust of Disappearance', '9', '1', '135', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This powder shimmers like a thousand tiny motes of light. Activating the dust by sprinkling it on yourself or a creature within reach casts a 4th-level <i>invisibility</i> spell with a duration of 1 minute on that creature. This invisibility can’t be negated or seen through by any spell of 3rd level or lower or any item of 5th level or lower.<br><br><b>Activate</b> 1 action Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=242'),
('RUNESTONE', 'consumables', 'Runestone', '1', NULL, '3', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This flat piece of hard stone is specially prepared for etching a magical fundamental rune or property rune. You can etch only one rune upon a stone. Once the stone is etched, it gains the magic school trait of the rune etched upon it. When a rune is transferred from the <i>runestone</i> to another object, the <i>runestone</i> cracks and is destroyed. The Price listed is for an empty stone; a stone holding a rune adds the Price of the rune.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=247'),
('CANDLE_OF_TRUTH', 'consumables', 'Candle of Truth', '8', '1', '75', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This tapered candle has a golden wick that burns with white fire. You activate the candle by lighting it, which causes creatures within 10 feet of the candle to find it difficult to tell falsehoods. Creatures in the area receive a –4 status penalty to Lie.<br><br> In addition, when first entering the affected area, each creature (including you) must succeed at a DC 26 Will save or be unable to tell any deliberate lies while within 10 feet of the lit candle. This lasts for as long as the candle is lit. Once lit, the candle burns for 10 minutes, and it cannot be extinguished.<br><br><b>Activate</b> 1 action Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=240'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_HOLLY_BUSH)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Holly Bush)', '2', '1', '6', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When this feather is activated, it immediately transforms into a living holly bush, filling a single square. This bush can provide standard cover. In addition, the bush has 2d4 bright-red berries. While holly berries are usually poisonous, these berries are infused with beneficial magic. You can pick and eat a berry as an Interact action to recover 1 Hit Point. Once plucked from the bush, a berry becomes non-magical after a few seconds, so it doesn’t heal you if you don’t eat it within the span of your Interact action.If activated on soil, the plant continues to grow and thrive (although it doesn’t produce any more healing berries). If activated elsewhere, it withers and dies within 1d4 days.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_SWAN_BOAT)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Swan Boat)', '8', '1', '76', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This feather can be activated only when tossed into a large body of water, such as a lake or broad river. It transforms into a swan-shaped boat capable of carrying up to 32 Medium creatures, 8 Large creatures, or 2 Huge creatures. The boat moves on the water at a Speed of 50 feet, and lasts 1 day.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_TREE)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Tree)', '6', '1', '38', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This token can be activated only on an unoccupied patch of earth or soil. When activated, this token transforms into an oak tree, 60 feet tall with a 5-foot-wide trunk. The tree continues to live and grow if conditions are favorable.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_ANCHOR)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Anchor)', '7', '1', '55', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This feather can be activated only on a boat. When activated, this feather transforms into a massive anchor that causes the boat to immediately stop. After 1 day, the anchor vanishes and the boat can move as normal. The anchor is attached to the boat by a magical chain of force, but the chain can be removed by dispel magic or destroyed (Hardness 30, HP 40).', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_WHIP)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Whip)', '9', '1', '130', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This feather transforms into a +1 striking dancing whip when activated. The whip immediately jumps from your grasp and proceeds to attack your enemies until 1 minute has passed or it fails its flat check for dancing, at which point it vanishes. If the whip’s target isn’t prone, the whip uses its actions to attempt to Trip that creature instead of making a Strike. The whip’s total attack modifier for Striking or Tripping is +18 instead of the normal bonus for a dancing weapon. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('DUST_OF_APPEARANCE', 'consumables', 'Dust of Appearance', '6', '1', '50', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Stored in a small reed, this powder looks like a fine metallic dust. When you fling it in the air, it coats all creatures in a 10-foot burst centered on a point within 5 feet of you. For 1 minute, the coated creatures can’t be concealed or invisible, nor can they benefit from <i>mirror image</i> or similar abilities that create illusory duplicates. Any illusions in the area of 3rd level or lower are revealed as such, although this does not end their effect.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  1 action Interact', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=241'),
('HOLY_WATER', 'consumables', 'Holy Water', '1', '1', '3', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This vial contains water blessed by a good deity. You activate a vial of <i>holy water</i> by throwing it as a Strike. It’s a simple thrown weapon with a range increment of 20 feet. Unlike an alchemical bomb, it doesn’t add the manipulate trait to the attack made with it.<br><br> <i>Holy water</i> deals 1d6 good damage and 1 good splash
damage. It damages only fiends, undead, and creatures that have a weakness to good damage.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Strike', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=245'),
('FEATHER_TOKEN_BIRD)', 'consumables', 'Feather Token (Bird)', '3', '1', '8', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When activated, this token transforms into a small sparrow that waits on your finger for you to relay a message up to 1 minute in length, along with the name and rough location of a recipient. The recipient must be someone you have met, and the location must be somewhere you have visited. After receiving the message, the bird flies off to deliver it, traveling at 30 miles per hour and then searching for the target in the location you provided. If the bird finds the target, it moves adjacent to them, your words emanate from the bird, and the bird then flies off and vanishes. The bird also vanishes if it fails to find your target after 10 hours of searching the location you specified.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=244'),
('SNAPLEAF', 'consumables', 'Snapleaf', '3', NULL, '9', NULL, '0', NULL, 'affixed to armor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small, crystalline carving takes the shape of a tree leaf and attaches to armor or clothing with a simple strap. When you activate the <i>snapleaf</i>, you gain the benefits of <i>feather fall</i> and a 2nd-level <i>invisibility</i> spell for 1 minute or until you stop falling, whichever comes first.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=512'),
('FORTIFYING_PEBBLE', 'consumables', 'Fortifying Pebble', '4', '-1', '13', NULL, '0', NULL, 'affixed to armor, shield, or weapon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small pebble is strangely dense and surprisingly durable, affixed to an object by a sturdy steel chain. When you activate the pebble, the affixed object takes 10 less damage.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  free action envision; <b>Trigger</b> The affixed object would take damage', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=522'),
('BEACON_SHOT', 'consumables', 'Beacon Shot', '3', '1', '10', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'arrow, bolt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The shaft of a <i>beacon shot</i> is studded with tiny flecks of glimmering gemstones. When an activated <i>beacon shot</i> hits a target, it embeds itself into that target and spews sparks for 1 minute. If the target is invisible, it becomes merely hidden to creatures who would otherwise be unable to see it. The sparks also negate the concealed condition if the target was otherwise concealed. <br><br> A creature can remove the arrow or bolt by using an Interact basic action and succeeding at a DC 20 Athletics check. <br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=159'),
('CLIMBING_BOLT', 'consumables', 'Climbing Bolt', '4', NULL, '15', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'bolt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The shaft of this bolt is wrapped with fine twine. When the bolt strikes a solid surface, the twine unwinds and enlarges into a 50-foot-long rope, securely fastened to the surface the bolt struck. The rope can be pulled free with an Interact action and a successful DC 20 Athletics check.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=160'),
('DISINTEGRATION_BOLT', 'consumables', 'Disintegration Bolt', '15', '1', '1300', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'bolt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The shaft of this bolt is scorched and blackened, and handling it coats your fingers with a fine black powder. When an activated <i>disintegration bolt</i> hits a target, it is subject to a <i>disintegrate</i> spell requiring a DC 34 Fortitude save. As with the spell, a critical hit on the attack roll causes the target’s saving throw outcome to be one degree worse.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Craft Requirements</b> Supply one casting of <i>disintegrate</i>.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=161'),
('EXPLOSIVE_AMMUNITION', 'consumables', 'Explosive Ammunition', '9', '1', '130', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This piece of ammunition is coated in gritty black soot. When activated <i>explosive ammunition</i> hits a target, the missile explodes in a 10-foot burst, dealing 6d6 fire damage to each creature in the area (including the target). Each creature must attempt a DC 25 basic Reflex save.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b> Explosive Ammunition Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 130 gp<br><br><b> Explosive Ammunition (Greater) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 520 gp<br>The damage is 10d6 and the save DC is 30.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=162'),
('EXPLOSIVE_AMMUNITION_GREATER)', 'consumables', 'Explosive Ammunition (Greater)', '13', '1', '520', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This piece of ammunition is coated in gritty black soot. When activated <i>explosive ammunition</i> hits a target, the missile explodes in a 10-foot burst, dealing 6d6 fire damage to each creature in the area (including the target). Each creature must attempt a DC 25 basic Reflex save.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b> Explosive Ammunition Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 130 gp<br><br><b> Explosive Ammunition (Greater) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 520 gp<br>The damage is 10d6 and the save DC is 30.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=162'),
('GHOST_AMMUNITION', 'consumables', 'Ghost Ammunition', '14', NULL, '900', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<i>Ghost ammunition</i> is cool to the touch. This ammunition has the benefits of the <i>ghost touch</i> property rune and can fly through any obstacle except those that can block incorporeal creatures or effects. Though the ammunition penetrates barriers and ignores all cover, the target still benefits from the flat check from being concealed or hidden. You still can’t target an undetected creature without guessing.<br><br> After it is launched, the ammunition vanishes into mist. However, in the dead of the night 1d4 days later, it reappears in the last quiver or other container it was taken from.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=163'),
('PENETRATING_AMMUNITION', 'consumables', 'Penetrating Ammunition', '12', '1', '400', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'arrow, bolt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This ammunition has a slender shape and a viciously pointed tip. When you activate and shoot <i>penetrating ammunition</i>, the Strike takes the shape of a 60-foot line originating from you. Roll one attack roll and compare the result to the AC of each target in the line. The ammunition ignores up to 10 of a target’s resistance, and it can penetrate walls up to 1 foot thick with Hardness 10 or less. Each target that takes damage from this ammunition also takes 1d6 persistent bleed damage.<br><br> If your attack roll result is a natural 20, you improve your degree of success only against the first target in the line, but you can still score a critical hit on other targets if your result exceeds their AC by 10 or more. If you have access to your bow’s critical specialization effect, penetrating ammunition applies that effect only against a target in the last square of the line.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=164'),
('SHINING_AMMUNITION', 'consumables', 'Shining Ammunition', '1', NULL, '3', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A piece of <i>shining ammunition</i> gives off a faint glow. When shot, this ammunition sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius (and dim light to the next 20 feet) for 10 minutes. If it hits a target, it sticks, causing the target to shed light in the same radius. A creature can remove the ammunition with an Interact action, but the ammunition itself continues to glow for the rest of the duration or until destroyed.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=165'),
('SLEEP_ARROW', 'consumables', 'Sleep Arrow', '3', '1', '11', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'arrow', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<i>Sleep arrows</i> often have shafts of deep blue or black, and their fletching is exceptionally soft and downy. An activated <i>sleep arrow</i> deals no damage, but a living creature hit by it is subject to the effects of a <i>sleep</i> spell (DC 17).<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Interact<br><br><b>Craft Requirements</b> Supply one casting of <i>sleep</i>.', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=166'),
('SPELLSTRIKE_AMMUNITION_TYPE_I)', 'consumables', 'Spellstrike Ammunition (Type I)', '3', '2', '12', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mystic patterns create a magic reservoir within this ammunition. You activate <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> by Casting a Spell into the ammunition. The spell must be of a spell level the ammunition can hold, and the spell must be able to target a creature other than the caster. A creature hit by activated <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> is targeted by the spell. If the creature isn’t a valid target for the spell, the spell is lost.<br><br> The ammunition affects only the target hit, even if the spell would normally affect more than one target. If the spell requires a spell attack roll, use the result of your ranged attack roll with the ammunition to determine the degree of success of the spell. If the spell requires a saving throw, the target attempts the save against your spell DC.<br><br> The maximum level of spell the ammunition can hold determines its item level and Price.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  2 actions Cast a Spell<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type I) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 1st<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type II) Item 5</b><br><b>Level</b> 5; <b>Price</b> 30 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 2nd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type III) Item 7</b><br><b>Level</b> 7; <b>Price</b> 70 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 3rd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IV) Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 150 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 4th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type V) Item 11</b><br><b>Level</b> 11; <b>Price</b> 300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 5th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VI) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 600 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 6th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VII) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 1,300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 7th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VIII) Item 17</b><br><b>Level</b> 17; <b>Price</b> 3,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 8th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IX) Item 19</b><br><b>Level</b> 19; <b>Price</b> 8,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 9th', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=167'),
('SPELLSTRIKE_AMMUNITION_TYPE_II)', 'consumables', 'Spellstrike Ammunition (Type II)', '5', '2', '30', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mystic patterns create a magic reservoir within this ammunition. You activate <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> by Casting a Spell into the ammunition. The spell must be of a spell level the ammunition can hold, and the spell must be able to target a creature other than the caster. A creature hit by activated <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> is targeted by the spell. If the creature isn’t a valid target for the spell, the spell is lost.<br><br> The ammunition affects only the target hit, even if the spell would normally affect more than one target. If the spell requires a spell attack roll, use the result of your ranged attack roll with the ammunition to determine the degree of success of the spell. If the spell requires a saving throw, the target attempts the save against your spell DC.<br><br> The maximum level of spell the ammunition can hold determines its item level and Price.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Cast a Spell<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type I) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 1st<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type II) Item 5</b><br><b>Level</b> 5; <b>Price</b> 30 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 2nd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type III) Item 7</b><br><b>Level</b> 7; <b>Price</b> 70 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 3rd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IV) Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 150 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 4th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type V) Item 11</b><br><b>Level</b> 11; <b>Price</b> 300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 5th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VI) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 600 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 6th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VII) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 1,300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 7th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VIII) Item 17</b><br><b>Level</b> 17; <b>Price</b> 3,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 8th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IX) Item 19</b><br><b>Level</b> 19; <b>Price</b> 8,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 9th', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=167'),
('SPELLSTRIKE_AMMUNITION_TYPE_III)', 'consumables', 'Spellstrike Ammunition (Type III)', '7', '2', '70', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mystic patterns create a magic reservoir within this ammunition. You activate <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> by Casting a Spell into the ammunition. The spell must be of a spell level the ammunition can hold, and the spell must be able to target a creature other than the caster. A creature hit by activated <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> is targeted by the spell. If the creature isn’t a valid target for the spell, the spell is lost.<br><br> The ammunition affects only the target hit, even if the spell would normally affect more than one target. If the spell requires a spell attack roll, use the result of your ranged attack roll with the ammunition to determine the degree of success of the spell. If the spell requires a saving throw, the target attempts the save against your spell DC.<br><br> The maximum level of spell the ammunition can hold determines its item level and Price.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Cast a Spell<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type I) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 1st<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type II) Item 5</b><br><b>Level</b> 5; <b>Price</b> 30 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 2nd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type III) Item 7</b><br><b>Level</b> 7; <b>Price</b> 70 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 3rd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IV) Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 150 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 4th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type V) Item 11</b><br><b>Level</b> 11; <b>Price</b> 300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 5th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VI) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 600 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 6th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VII) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 1,300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 7th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VIII) Item 17</b><br><b>Level</b> 17; <b>Price</b> 3,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 8th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IX) Item 19</b><br><b>Level</b> 19; <b>Price</b> 8,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 9th', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=167'),
('SPELLSTRIKE_AMMUNITION_TYPE_IV)', 'consumables', 'Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IV)', '9', '2', '150', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mystic patterns create a magic reservoir within this ammunition. You activate <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> by Casting a Spell into the ammunition. The spell must be of a spell level the ammunition can hold, and the spell must be able to target a creature other than the caster. A creature hit by activated <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> is targeted by the spell. If the creature isn’t a valid target for the spell, the spell is lost.<br><br> The ammunition affects only the target hit, even if the spell would normally affect more than one target. If the spell requires a spell attack roll, use the result of your ranged attack roll with the ammunition to determine the degree of success of the spell. If the spell requires a saving throw, the target attempts the save against your spell DC.<br><br> The maximum level of spell the ammunition can hold determines its item level and Price.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Cast a Spell<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type I) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 1st<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type II) Item 5</b><br><b>Level</b> 5; <b>Price</b> 30 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 2nd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type III) Item 7</b><br><b>Level</b> 7; <b>Price</b> 70 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 3rd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IV) Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 150 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 4th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type V) Item 11</b><br><b>Level</b> 11; <b>Price</b> 300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 5th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VI) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 600 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 6th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VII) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 1,300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 7th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VIII) Item 17</b><br><b>Level</b> 17; <b>Price</b> 3,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 8th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IX) Item 19</b><br><b>Level</b> 19; <b>Price</b> 8,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 9th', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=167'),
('SPELLSTRIKE_AMMUNITION_TYPE_IX)', 'consumables', 'Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IX)', '19', '2', '8000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'any ammunition', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Mystic patterns create a magic reservoir within this ammunition. You activate <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> by Casting a Spell into the ammunition. The spell must be of a spell level the ammunition can hold, and the spell must be able to target a creature other than the caster. A creature hit by activated <i>spellstrike ammunition</i> is targeted by the spell. If the creature isn’t a valid target for the spell, the spell is lost.<br><br> The ammunition affects only the target hit, even if the spell would normally affect more than one target. If the spell requires a spell attack roll, use the result of your ranged attack roll with the ammunition to determine the degree of success of the spell. If the spell requires a saving throw, the target attempts the save against your spell DC.<br><br> The maximum level of spell the ammunition can hold determines its item level and Price.<br><br><b>Activate</b>  Cast a Spell<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type I) Item 3</b><br><b>Level</b> 3; <b>Price</b> 12 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 1st<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type II) Item 5</b><br><b>Level</b> 5; <b>Price</b> 30 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 2nd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type III) Item 7</b><br><b>Level</b> 7; <b>Price</b> 70 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 3rd<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IV) Item 9</b><br><b>Level</b> 9; <b>Price</b> 150 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 4th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type V) Item 11</b><br><b>Level</b> 11; <b>Price</b> 300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 5th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VI) Item 13</b><br><b>Level</b> 13; <b>Price</b> 600 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 6th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VII) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 1,300 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 7th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type VIII) Item 17</b><br><b>Level</b> 17; <b>Price</b> 3,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 8th<br><br><b> Spellstrike Ammunition (Type IX) Item 19</b><br><b>Level</b> 19; <b>Price</b> 8,000 gp<br>Maximum Spell Level 9th', NULL, 'http://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=167'),
