 is being used as a beast of burden or for transport. If it attempts an attack or otherwise engages in combat, it reverts to statuette form after 1d4 rounds.<br><br><b>Wondrous Figurine (Obsidian Steed) Item 15</b><br><b>Level</b> 15; <b>Price</b> 6,000 gp<br>This sinister-looking black statuette resembles a horse rearing up on its hind legs. When activated, this figurine becomes a nightmare. It can be called upon once per week for up to 24 hours, though it won’t use <i>plane shift or its other abilities on behalf of its rider. Although evil, it allows itself to be ridden by creatures of any alignment, although if a good creature mounts it, the rider must attempt a DC 3 flat check. On a failure, the nightmare uses <i>plane shift to take the rider to a random location in the Abyss, where it promptly returns to statue form, stranding its rider in that nightmarish place.<br><br><b>Wondrous Figurine (Onyx Dog) Item 2</b><br><b>Level</b> 2; <b>Price</b> 34 gp<br>This simple onyx statue transforms into a guard dog. The dog has a +4 circumstance bonus to Survival checks to Track, and it has darkvision. When the dog senses a hidden creature with its scent, that creature is instead observed and concealed. The onyx dog can be activated once per week and remains in its form for up to 6 hours.', NULL, NULL, 'Each one of these statuettes is 1 inch in height, carved from a specific material and taking the shape of a particular animal or animals.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=270'),
('DRAGON_S_EYE_CHARM', 'held', 'Dragon''s Eye Charm', '7', '1', '360.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '1', 'Interact; Frequency once per day; Effect The dragon’s eye charm manifests fire for you to wield against your foe. You cast a 5th-level produce flame spell with a spell attack roll of +13.

Activate Single Action Interact; Frequency once per day; Effect The charm’s pupil becomes plainly visible. You can look through the charm to gain darkvision for as long as you Sustain the Activation, to a maximum of 10 minutes.

Activate Single Action Interact; Frequency once per day; Effect The dragon’s eye charm shrouds you in a faintly glowing layer of golden energy. You gain fire resistance 5 for 10 minutes.

Activate Single Action Interact; Frequency once per day; Effect You can speak and understand Draconic as long as you Sustain the Activation, to a maximum of 10 minutes.', NULL, NULL, 'This charm, a dragon-shaped pendant worn like a necklace or set into armor or clothing as a decoration, is warm and smooth to the touch. It must be held in one hand to be used (pressing the palm of one’s hand to the charm also works, provided that your hand is otherwise empty). It has four distinct powers.', 'Cult of Cinders', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=502'),
('OCCULT_SCROLL_CASE_OF_SIMPLICITY', 'held', 'Occult Scroll Case of Simplicity', '4', '1', '100', NULL, '0', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '1', 'Interact; <b>Requirements</b> The scroll case contains a single scroll of a 1st-level spell; <b>Effect</b> You transfer the scroll’s energy into the scroll case, consuming the scroll, and you can immediately begin casting one of the scroll case’s spells. If you use any action other than to Cast a Spell from the scroll case after activating the <i>scroll case of simplicity</i>, the scroll and its energy are lost.', NULL, NULL, 'The four different types of <i>scroll cases of simplicity</i> often bear adornments appropriate to their magical tradition, such as angelic wings or otherworldly lettering. On the inside, intricate runic diagrams spiral out to surround the scroll stored within. A scroll placed within the case can be converted into energy to cast consistently useful spells depending on its type. You must be able to cast spells of a given tradition to use a <i>scroll case of simplicity</i> of a corresponding type.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=525'),
('DIVINE_SCROLL_CASE_OF_SIMPLICITY', 'held', 'Divine Scroll Case of Simplicity', '4', '1', '100', NULL, '0', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '1', 'Interact; <b>Requirements</b> The scroll case contains a single scroll of a 1st-level spell; <b>Effect</b> You transfer the scroll’s energy into the scroll case, consuming the scroll, and you can immediately begin casting one of the scroll case’s spells. If you use any action other than to Cast a Spell from the scroll case after activating the <i>scroll case of simplicity</i>, the scroll and its energy are lost.', NULL, NULL, 'The four different types of <i>scroll cases of simplicity</i> often bear adornments appropriate to their magical tradition, such as angelic wings or otherworldly lettering. On the inside, intricate runic diagrams spiral out to surround the scroll stored within. A scroll placed within the case can be converted into energy to cast consistently useful spells depending on its type. You must be able to cast spells of a given tradition to use a <i>scroll case of simplicity</i> of a corresponding type.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=525'),
('ARCANE_SCROLL_CASE_OF_SIMPLICITY', 'held', 'Arcane Scroll Case of Simplicity', '4', '1', '100', NULL, '0', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '1', 'Interact; <b>Requirements</b> The scroll case contains a single scroll of a 1st-level spell; <b>Effect</b> You transfer the scroll’s energy into the scroll case, consuming the scroll, and you can immediately begin casting one of the scroll case’s spells. If you use any action other than to Cast a Spell from the scroll case after activating the <i>scroll case of simplicity</i>, the scroll and its energy are lost.', NULL, NULL, 'The four different types of <i>scroll cases of simplicity</i> often bear adornments appropriate to their magical tradition, such as angelic wings or otherworldly lettering. On the inside, intricate runic diagrams spiral out to surround the scroll stored within. A scroll placed within the case can be converted into energy to cast consistently useful spells depending on its type. You must be able to cast spells of a given tradition to use a <i>scroll case of simplicity</i> of a corresponding type.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=525'),
('PRIMAL_SCROLL_CASE_OF_SIMPLICITY', 'held', 'Primal Scroll Case of Simplicity', '4', '1', '100', NULL, '0', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '1', 'Interact; <b>Requirements</b> The scroll case contains a single scroll of a 1st-level spell; <b>Effect</b> You transfer the scroll’s energy into the scroll case, consuming the scroll, and you can immediately begin casting one of the scroll case’s spells. If you use any action other than to Cast a Spell from the scroll case after activating the <i>scroll case of simplicity</i>, the scroll and its energy are lost.', NULL, NULL, 'The four different types of <i>scroll cases of simplicity</i> often bear adornments appropriate to their magical tradition, such as angelic wings or otherworldly lettering. On the inside, intricate runic diagrams spiral out to surround the scroll stored within. A scroll placed within the case can be converted into energy to cast consistently useful spells depending on its type. You must be able to cast spells of a given tradition to use a <i>scroll case of simplicity</i> of a corresponding type.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=525'),
('INSISTENT_DOOR_KNOCKER', 'held', 'Insistent Door Knocker', '6', '2', '225', NULL, '1', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '2', 'command, Interact; <b>Frequency</b> once per day; <b>Effect</b> You place the door knocker against a wall, floor, or ceiling. The door knocker fuses in place and creates a usable door within the surface. Any creature can move through the door normally, as if the door had always been there. The door can penetrate up to 1 foot of material, so thick material, such as heavy stone walls, can cause this effect to fail, expending its use for the day. A thin layer of metal in a wall, floor, or ceiling also causes the effect to fail. You can use an Interact action to release the door knocker from the surface and return the surface to its previous shape.', NULL, NULL, 'This dark iron door knocker comes in a variety of shapes, such as a bird clutching a ring in its talons or a gargoyle holding a ring in its mouth. Placing the door knocker on the surface of a door (an Interact action) causes it to attach and remain in place. While in place, the door knocker whispers hints to you while you attempt to unlock the door, granting a +1 item bonus to Thievery checks to Pick a Lock. Removing the door knocker from a surface requires you to use an Interact action.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=511'),
('GREATER_INSISTENT_DOOR_KNOCKER', 'held', 'Greater Insistent Door Knocker', '11', '2', '1250', NULL, '1', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '2', 'command, Interact; <b>Frequency</b> once per day; <b>Effect</b> You place the door knocker against a wall, floor, or ceiling. The door knocker fuses in place and creates a usable door within the surface. Any creature can move through the door normally, as if the door had always been there. The door can penetrate up to 1 foot of material, so thick material, such as heavy stone walls, can cause this effect to fail, expending its use for the day. A thin layer of metal in a wall, floor, or ceiling also causes the effect to fail. You can use an Interact action to release the door knocker from the surface and return the surface to its previous shape.', NULL, NULL, 'This dark iron door knocker comes in a variety of shapes, such as a bird clutching a ring in its talons or a gargoyle holding a ring in its mouth. Placing the door knocker on the surface of a door (an Interact action) causes it to attach and remain in place. While in place, the door knocker whispers hints to you while you attempt to unlock the door, granting a +1 item bonus to Thievery checks to Pick a Lock. Removing the door knocker from a surface requires you to use an Interact action.<br><br>The item bonus is +2, and the door knocker can penetrate up to 5 feet of material when activated.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=511'),
('MAJOR_INSISTENT_DOOR_KNOCKER', 'held', 'Major Insistent Door Knocker', '17', '2', '13500', NULL, '1', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '2', 'command, Interact; <b>Frequency</b> once per day; <b>Effect</b> You place the door knocker against a wall, floor, or ceiling. The door knocker fuses in place and creates a usable door within the surface. Any creature can move through the door normally, as if the door had always been there. The door can penetrate up to 1 foot of material, so thick material, such as heavy stone walls, can cause this effect to fail, expending its use for the day. A thin layer of metal in a wall, floor, or ceiling also causes the effect to fail. You can use an Interact action to release the door knocker from the surface and return the surface to its previous shape.', NULL, NULL, 'This dark iron door knocker comes in a variety of shapes, such as a bird clutching a ring in its talons or a gargoyle holding a ring in its mouth. Placing the door knocker on the surface of a door (an Interact action) causes it to attach and remain in place. While in place, the door knocker whispers hints to you while you attempt to unlock the door, granting a +1 item bonus to Thievery checks to Pick a Lock. Removing the door knocker from a surface requires you to use an Interact action.<br><br>The item bonus is +3, and the door knocker can penetrate up to 10 feet of material when activated.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=511'),
('PATHFINDER_S_COIN', 'held', 'Pathfinder''s Coin', '2', '1', '30', NULL, '0', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '1', 'command; <b>Requirements</b> The coin is levitating above a <i>wayfinder
 <!--/i-->; <b>Effect</b> You give the coin a message of 25 words or fewer. The message repeats in your voice the next time the coin is floated above a <i>wayfinder</i>. A <i>Pathfinder’s coin</i> can hold only one message at a time, and it replays its message only once.</i>', NULL, NULL, 'This coin usually resembles ancient currency. An intricate matrix of gold and platinum wires inside the coin causes it to float an inch in the air and spin if placed on a <i>wayfinder</i>.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=523'),
('PATHFINDER_CHRONICLE', 'held', 'Pathfinder Chronicle', '3', NULL, '6', NULL, 'L', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Numerous volumes and editions of the Pathfinder Chronicles exist, each cataloging different adventures. Pathfinder Chronicles are a type of scholarly journal that specifically devotes topics to Pathfinder discoveries, rather than more theoretical academic topics. Because Pathfinders have better access to these chronicles than other scholarly journals, they are particularly common among Pathfinder agents building a library of reference texts.', 'Lost Omens Character Guide', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=64'),
('GUIDING_CHISEL', 'held', 'Guiding Chisel', '16', NULL, '10000', NULL, '1', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You gain a +3 item bonus to Crafting checks related to stonemasonry. In addition, it takes you only 1 day to Craft items using the <i>Guiding Chisel</i> instead of 4 days, and you quadruple the discount you get for spending additional days Crafting items with the <i>Guiding Chisel</i>. If it’s unclear whether you could use the <i>Guiding Chisel</i> to Craft an item, the GM decides.', 'Fires of the Haunted City', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=541'),
('ORB_SHARD', 'held', 'Orb Shard', '20', '3', '0', NULL, '1', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A shard of the Orb of Gold Dragonkind resembles a pointed length of crystal about the size and shape of a shortsword without a hilt. It functions as a +3 striking shortsword that deals 2d6 extra damage to dragons.<br><br>Each orb shard within 60 feet of the flawed orb of Gold Dragonkind increases the save DC against the orb by 1; thus, if all 13 remaining orb shards are in this area, the save DC against the flawed orb increases from DC 30 to DC 43. A talented spellcaster or crafter can integrate an orb shard back into the flawed orb to make this DC increase permanent.', 'Broken Promises', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=561'),
('FLAWED_ORB_OF_GOLD_DRAGONKIND', 'held', 'Flawed Orb of Gold Dragonkind', '25', '3', '0', NULL, '1', NULL, 'held in 1 hand', NULL, '3', 'envision, Interact; <b>Frequency</b> Three times per day; <b>Effect</b> You attempt to overwhelm a dragon’s mind—while you cannot control the dragon, you can render it immobile for a short time. Choose a dragon within 60 feet; the dragon can attempt to resist the orb with a DC 30 Will saving throw (or higher with <i>orb shards</i>). Gold dragons take a –4 circumstance penalty to this saving throw. Any stun from this activation ends if the dragon is attacked or otherwise subject to a hostile act other than that of the orb.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> The dragon is unaffected.<br><b>Success</b> The dragon is stunned 3.<br><b>Failure</b> The dragon is stunned for as long as the orb’s wielder Sustains the Activation.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> As failure, but hostile actions don’t end the dragon’s stun. Destruction The <i>Flawed Orb of Gold Dragonkind</i> is resilient, but its imperfect nature leaves it vulnerable. It can be damaged or even destroyed by mundane attacks (Hardness 40, HP 200, BT 100). It has weakness 30 to the Breath Weapons and Strikes of gold dragons.', NULL, NULL, 'Each of the legendary Orbs of Dragonkind contains the essence and personality of a powerful dragon. The Orb of Gold Dragonkind was the most powerful of them all, until it was shattered by Mengkare’s draconic breath. Reconstructed at great expense by enslaved spellcasters toiling under the Scarlet Triad’s watch, the Flawed Orb of Gold Dragonkind is a shadow of its prior self, yet it remains a potent weapon against dragons of all types.<br><br>While carried, the Flawed Orb of Gold Dragonkind grants its owner resistance 30 to the Breath Weapons of gold dragons. The owner also can sense if there are any dragons within 10 miles, or any gold dragons within 100 miles. When within 1 mile of a dragon, they can determine the direction to the dragon and the dragon’s age category (such as young, ancient, or wyrm).
', 'Broken Promises', 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=561'),
('ADVENTURER_S_PACK', 'equipment', 'Adventurer''s Pack', '0', NULL, '0.7', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This item is the starter kit for an adventurer, containing the essential items for exploration and survival. The Bulk value is for the entire pack together, but see the descriptions of individual items as necessary.<br><br> The pack contains the following items: backpack (containing the other goods), bedroll, two belt pouches, 10 pieces of chalk, flint and steel, 50 feet of rope, 2 weeks’ rations, soap, 5 torches, and a waterskin.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=1'),
('ALCHEMIST_S_TOOLS', 'equipment', 'Alchemist''s Tools', '0', NULL, '3.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This mobile collection of vials and chemicals can be used for simple alchemical tasks.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=2'),
('ALCHEMIST_S_LAB_EXPANDED)', 'equipment', 'Alchemist''s Lab (Expanded)', '3', NULL, '55.0', NULL, '6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need an alchemist’s lab to Craft alchemical items during downtime. An expanded alchemist’s lab gives a +1 item bonus to Crafting checks to create alchemical items.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=2'),
('ARROWS', 'equipment', 'Arrows', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, '10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Weapons.aspx'),
('ARTISAN_S_TOOLS', 'equipment', 'Artisan''s Tools', '0', NULL, '4.0', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need these tools to create items from raw materials with the Craft skill. Sterling artisan’s tools give you a +1 item bonus to the check. Different sets are needed for different work, as determined by the GM; for example, blacksmith’s tools differ from woodworker’s&nbsp;tools.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=3'),
('ARTISAN_S_TOOLS_STERLING)', 'equipment', 'Artisan''s Tools (Sterling)', '3', NULL, '50.0', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need these tools to create items from raw materials with the Craft skill. Sterling artisan’s tools give you a +1 item bonus to the check. Different sets are needed for different work, as determined by the GM; for example, blacksmith’s tools differ from woodworker’s&nbsp;tools.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=3'),
('BACKPACK', 'equipment', 'Backpack', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, NULL, '4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A backpack holds up to 4 Bulk of items. If you’re carrying or stowing the pack rather than wearing it on your back, its bulk is light instead of negligible. The first 2 Bulk of items in your backpack don’t count against your Bulk limits.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=4'),
('BANDOLIER', 'equipment', 'Bandolier', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, NULL, '0.8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A bandolier holds up to eight items of light Bulk within easy reach and is usually used for alchemical items or potions. If you are carrying or stowing a bandolier rather than wearing it around your chest, it has light Bulk instead of negligible. A bandolier can be dedicated to a full set of tools, such as healer’s tools, allowing you to draw the tools as part of the action that requires them.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=5'),
('BASIC_CRAFTER_S_BOOK', 'equipment', 'Basic Crafter''s Book', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This book contains the formulas (page 293) for Crafting the common items in this chapter.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=6'),
('BEDROLL', 'equipment', 'Bedroll', '0', NULL, '0.01', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=7'),
('BELT_POUCH', 'equipment', 'Belt Pouch', '0', NULL, '0.04', NULL, NULL, '0.4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A belt pouch holds up to four items of light&nbsp;Bulk.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=8'),
('BLOWGUN_DARTS', 'equipment', 'Blowgun Darts', '0', NULL, '0.05', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, '10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Weapons.aspx'),
('BOLTS', 'equipment', 'Bolts', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, '10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Weapons.aspx'),
('CALTROPS', 'equipment', 'Caltrops', '0', NULL, '0.3', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'These four-pronged metal spikes can cause damage to a creature’s feet. You can scatter caltrops in an empty square adjacent to you with an Interact action. The first creature that moves into that square must succeed at a DC 14 Acrobatics check or take 1d4 piercing damage and 1 persistent bleed damage. A creature taking persistent bleed damage from caltrops takes a –5-foot penalty to its Speed. Spending an Interact action to pluck the caltrops free reduces the DC to stop the bleeding. Once a creature takes damage from caltrops, enough caltrops are ruined that other creatures moving into the square are safe.<br><br> Deployed caltrops can be salvaged and reused if no creatures took damage from them. Otherwise, enough caltrops are ruined that they can’t be salvaged.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=9'),
('CANDLE', 'equipment', 'Candle', '0', NULL, '0.01', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A lit candle sheds dim light in a 10-foot radius.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=10'),
('CHAIN', 'equipment', 'Chain', '0', NULL, '4.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=11'),
('CHALK', 'equipment', 'Chalk', '0', NULL, '0.01', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=12'),
('CHEST', 'equipment', 'Chest', '0', NULL, '0.6', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A wooden chest can hold up to 8 Bulk of items.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=13'),
('CLIMBING_KIT', 'equipment', 'Climbing Kit', '0', NULL, '0.5', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This satchel includes 50 feet of rope, pulleys, a dozen pitons, a hammer, a grappling hook, and one set of crampons. Climbing kits allow you to attach yourself to the wall you’re Climbing, moving half as quickly as usual (minimum 5 feet) but letting you attempt a DC 5 flat check whenever you critically fail to prevent a fall. You gain a +1 item bonus to Athletics checks to Climb while using an extreme climbing kit. A single kit has only enough materials for one climber; each climber needs their own kit.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=14'),
('CLIMBING_KIT_EXTREME)', 'equipment', 'Climbing Kit (Extreme)', '3', NULL, '40.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This satchel includes 50 feet of rope, pulleys, a dozen pitons, a hammer, a grappling hook, and one set of crampons. Climbing kits allow you to attach yourself to the wall you’re Climbing, moving half as quickly as usual (minimum 5 feet) but letting you attempt a DC 5 flat check whenever you critically fail to prevent a fall. You gain a +1 item bonus to Athletics checks to Climb while using an extreme climbing kit. A single kit has only enough materials for one climber; each climber needs their own kit.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=14'),
('CLOTHING_EXPLORER_S)', 'equipment', 'Clothing (Explorer''s)', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=15'),
('CLOTHING_FINE)', 'equipment', 'Clothing (Fine)', '0', NULL, '2.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=15'),
('CLOTHING_HIGH_FASHION_FINE)', 'equipment', 'Clothing (High-Fashion Fine)', '3', NULL, '55.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=15'),
('CLOTHING_ORDINARY)', 'equipment', 'Clothing (Ordinary)', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=15'),
('CLOTHING_WINTER)', 'equipment', 'Clothing (Winter)', '0', NULL, '0.4', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=15'),
('COMPASS', 'equipment', 'Compass', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A compass helps you Sense Direction or navigate, provided you’re in&nbsp;a location with uniform magnetic fields. Without a compass, you take a –2 item penalty to these checks (similar to using a shoddy item). A lensatic compass gives you a&nbsp;+1 item bonus to&nbsp;these checks.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=16'),
('COMPASS_LENSATIC)', 'equipment', 'Compass (Lensatic)', '3', NULL, '20.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A compass helps you Sense Direction or navigate, provided you’re in&nbsp;a location with uniform magnetic fields. Without a compass, you take a –2 item penalty to these checks (similar to using a shoddy item). A lensatic compass gives you a&nbsp;+1 item bonus to&nbsp;these checks.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=16'),
('COOKWARE', 'equipment', 'Cookware', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=17'),
('CROWBAR', 'equipment', 'Crowbar', '0', NULL, '0.5', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When Forcing Open an object that doesn’t have an easy grip, a crowbar makes it easier to gain the necessary leverage. Without a crowbar, prying something open takes a –2 item penalty to the Athletics check to Force Open (similar to using a shoddy item). A levered crowbar grants you a +1 item bonus to Athletics checks to Force Open anything that can be pried open. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=18'),
('CROWBAR_LEVERED)', 'equipment', 'Crowbar (Levered)', '3', NULL, '20.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When Forcing Open an object that doesn’t have an easy grip, a crowbar makes it easier to gain the necessary leverage. Without a crowbar, prying something open takes a –2 item penalty to the Athletics check to Force Open (similar to using a shoddy item). A levered crowbar grants you a +1 item bonus to Athletics checks to Force Open anything that can be pried open. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=18'),
('DISGUISE_KIT', 'equipment', 'Disguise Kit', '0', NULL, '2.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small wooden box contains cosmetics, false facial hair, spirit gum, and a few simple wigs. You usually need a disguise kit to set up a disguise in order to Impersonate someone using the Deception skill. An elite disguise kit adds a +1 item bonus to relevant checks. If you’ve crafted a large number of disguises, you can replenish your cosmetics supply with replacement cosmetics suitable for the type of your disguise kit.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=19'),
('DISGUISE_KIT_ELITE_COSMETICS)', 'equipment', 'Disguise Kit (Elite Cosmetics)', '3', NULL, '0.5', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small wooden box contains cosmetics, false facial hair, spirit gum, and a few simple wigs. You usually need a disguise kit to set up a disguise in order to Impersonate someone using the Deception skill. An elite disguise kit adds a +1 item bonus to relevant checks. If you’ve crafted a large number of disguises, you can replenish your cosmetics supply with replacement cosmetics suitable for the type of your disguise kit.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=19'),
('DISGUISE_KIT_ELITE)', 'equipment', 'Disguise Kit (Elite)', '3', NULL, '40.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small wooden box contains cosmetics, false facial hair, spirit gum, and a few simple wigs. You usually need a disguise kit to set up a disguise in order to Impersonate someone using the Deception skill. An elite disguise kit adds a +1 item bonus to relevant checks. If you’ve crafted a large number of disguises, you can replenish your cosmetics supply with replacement cosmetics suitable for the type of your disguise kit.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=19'),
('DISGUISE_KIT_REPLACEMENT_COSMETICS)', 'equipment', 'Disguise Kit (Replacement Cosmetics)', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This small wooden box contains cosmetics, false facial hair, spirit gum, and a few simple wigs. You usually need a disguise kit to set up a disguise in order to Impersonate someone using the Deception skill. An elite disguise kit adds a +1 item bonus to relevant checks. If you’ve crafted a large number of disguises, you can replenish your cosmetics supply with replacement cosmetics suitable for the type of your disguise kit.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=19'),
('FISHING_TACKLE', 'equipment', 'Fishing Tackle', '0', NULL, '0.8', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit include a collapsible fishing pole, fishhooks, line, lures, and a fishing net. Professional fishing tackle grants a +1 item bonus to checks to fish.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=20'),
('FISHING_TACKLE_PROFESSIONAL)', 'equipment', 'Fishing Tackle (Professional)', '3', NULL, '20.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit include a collapsible fishing pole, fishhooks, line, lures, and a fishing net. Professional fishing tackle grants a +1 item bonus to checks to fish.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=20'),
('FLINT_AND_STEEL', 'equipment', 'Flint and Steel', '0', NULL, '0.05', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Flint and steel are useful in creating a fire if you have the time to catch a spark, though using them is typically too time-consuming to be practical during an encounter. Even in ideal conditions, using flint and steel to light a flame requires using at least 3 actions, and often significantly longer.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=21'),
('FORMULA_BOOK_BLANK)', 'equipment', 'Formula Book (Blank)', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A formula book holds the formulas necessary to make items other than the common equipment from this chapter; alchemists typically get one for free. Each formula book can hold the formulas for up to 100 different items. Formulas can also appear on parchment sheets, tablets, and almost any other medium; there’s no need for you to copy them into a specific book as long as you can keep them on hand to reference them.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=22'),
('GRAPPLING_HOOK', 'equipment', 'Grappling Hook', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can throw a grappling hook with a rope tied to it to make a climb easier. To anchor a grappling hook, make an attack roll with the secret trait against a DC depending on the target, typically at least DC 20. On a success, your hook has a firm hold, but on a critical failure, the hook seems like it will hold but actually falls when you’re partway up.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=23'),
('HAMMER', 'equipment', 'Hammer', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=24'),
('HEALER_S_TOOLS', 'equipment', 'Healer''s Tools', '0', NULL, '5.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit of bandages, herbs, and suturing tools is necessary for Medicine checks to Administer First Aid, Treat Disease, Treat Poison, or Treat Wounds. Expanded healer’s tools provide a +1 item bonus to such checks. When you carry the tools from place to place, you keep many of the components handy on your person, in pockets or&nbsp;bandoliers.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=25'),
('HEALER_S_TOOLS_EXPANDED)', 'equipment', 'Healer''s Tools (Expanded)', '3', NULL, '50.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit of bandages, herbs, and suturing tools is necessary for Medicine checks to Administer First Aid, Treat Disease, Treat Poison, or Treat Wounds. Expanded healer’s tools provide a +1 item bonus to such checks. When you carry the tools from place to place, you keep many of the components handy on your person, in pockets or&nbsp;bandoliers.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=25'),
('HOLLY_AND_MISTLETOE', 'equipment', 'Holly and Mistletoe', '0', NULL, '0', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Plants of supernatural significance provide a primal focus for primal spellcasters, such as druids, when using certain abilities and casting some spells. A bundle of holly and mistletoe must be held in one hand to use it. Other primal foci exist for druids focused on other aspects of nature.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=26'),
('HOURGLASS', 'equipment', 'Hourglass', '0', NULL, '3.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=27'),
('LADDER', 'equipment', 'Ladder', '0', NULL, '0.03', NULL, '3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=28'),
('LANTERN_BULL_S_EYE)', 'equipment', 'Lantern (Bull''s-Eye)', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A lantern sheds bright light and requires 1 pint of oil to function for 6 hours.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=29'),
('LANTERN_HOODED)', 'equipment', 'Lantern (Hooded)', '0', NULL, '0.7', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A lantern sheds bright light and requires 1 pint of oil to function for 6 hours.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=29'),
('LOCK_AVERAGE)', 'equipment', 'Lock (Average)', '3', NULL, '15.0', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Picking a poor lock requires two successful DC 15 Thievery checks, a simple lock requires three successful DC&nbsp;20 Thievery checks, an average lock requires four successes at DC 25, a good lock requires five successes at DC 30, and a superior lock six successes at DC 40.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=30'),
('LOCK_GOOD)', 'equipment', 'Lock (Good)', '9', NULL, '200.0', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Picking a poor lock requires two successful DC 15 Thievery checks, a simple lock requires three successful DC&nbsp;20 Thievery checks, an average lock requires four successes at DC 25, a good lock requires five successes at DC 30, and a superior lock six successes at DC 40.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=30'),
('LOCK_POOR)', 'equipment', 'Lock (Poor)', '0', NULL, '0.2', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Picking a poor lock requires two successful DC 15 Thievery checks, a simple lock requires three successful DC&nbsp;20 Thievery checks, an average lock requires four successes at DC 25, a good lock requires five successes at DC 30, and a superior lock six successes at DC 40.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=30'),
('LOCK_SIMPLE)', 'equipment', 'Lock (Simple)', '1', NULL, '2.0', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Picking a poor lock requires two successful DC 15 Thievery checks, a simple lock requires three successful DC&nbsp;20 Thievery checks, an average lock requires four successes at DC 25, a good lock requires five successes at DC 30, and a superior lock six successes at DC 40.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=30'),
('LOCK_SUPERIOR)', 'equipment', 'Lock (Superior)', '17', NULL, '4500', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Picking a poor lock requires two successful DC 15 Thievery checks, a simple lock requires three successful DC&nbsp;20 Thievery checks, an average lock requires four successes at DC 25, a good lock requires five successes at DC 30, and a superior lock six successes at DC 40.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=30'),
('MAGNIFYING_GLASS', 'equipment', 'Magnifying Glass', '0', NULL, '40.0', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This quality handheld lens gives you a +1 item bonus to Perception checks to notice minute details of documents, fabric, and the like.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=31'),
('MANACLES_AVERAGE)', 'equipment', 'Manacles (Average)', '3', NULL, '20.0', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can manacle someone who is willing or otherwise at your mercy as an exploration activity taking 10–30 seconds depending on the creature’s size and how many manacles you apply. A two-legged creature with its legs bound takes a –15-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds, and a two-handed creature with its wrists bound has to succeed at a DC 5 flat check any time it uses a manipulate action or else that action fails. This DC may be higher depending on how tightly the manacles constrain the hands. A creature bound to a stationary object is immobilized. For creatures with more or fewer limbs, the GM determines what effect manacles have, if any. Freeing a creature from poor manacles requires two successful DC 17 Thievery checks, simple manacles requires three successes at DC 22, average manacles require four successes at DC&nbsp;27, good manacles require five successes at DC 32, and superior manacles require six successes at DC 42.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=32'),
('MANACLES_GOOD)', 'equipment', 'Manacles (Good)', '9', NULL, '250.0', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can manacle someone who is willing or otherwise at your mercy as an exploration activity taking 10–30 seconds depending on the creature’s size and how many manacles you apply. A two-legged creature with its legs bound takes a –15-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds, and a two-handed creature with its wrists bound has to succeed at a DC 5 flat check any time it uses a manipulate action or else that action fails. This DC may be higher depending on how tightly the manacles constrain the hands. A creature bound to a stationary object is immobilized. For creatures with more or fewer limbs, the GM determines what effect manacles have, if any. Freeing a creature from poor manacles requires two successful DC 17 Thievery checks, simple manacles requires three successes at DC 22, average manacles require four successes at DC&nbsp;27, good manacles require five successes at DC 32, and superior manacles require six successes at DC 42.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=32'),
('MANACLES_POOR)', 'equipment', 'Manacles (Poor)', '0', NULL, '0.3', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can manacle someone who is willing or otherwise at your mercy as an exploration activity taking 10–30 seconds depending on the creature’s size and how many manacles you apply. A two-legged creature with its legs bound takes a –15-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds, and a two-handed creature with its wrists bound has to succeed at a DC 5 flat check any time it uses a manipulate action or else that action fails. This DC may be higher depending on how tightly the manacles constrain the hands. A creature bound to a stationary object is immobilized. For creatures with more or fewer limbs, the GM determines what effect manacles have, if any. Freeing a creature from poor manacles requires two successful DC 17 Thievery checks, simple manacles requires three successes at DC 22, average manacles require four successes at DC&nbsp;27, good manacles require five successes at DC 32, and superior manacles require six successes at DC 42.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=32'),
('MANACLES_SIMPLE)', 'equipment', 'Manacles (Simple)', '1', NULL, '3.0', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can manacle someone who is willing or otherwise at your mercy as an exploration activity taking 10–30 seconds depending on the creature’s size and how many manacles you apply. A two-legged creature with its legs bound takes a –15-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds, and a two-handed creature with its wrists bound has to succeed at a DC 5 flat check any time it uses a manipulate action or else that action fails. This DC may be higher depending on how tightly the manacles constrain the hands. A creature bound to a stationary object is immobilized. For creatures with more or fewer limbs, the GM determines what effect manacles have, if any. Freeing a creature from poor manacles requires two successful DC 17 Thievery checks, simple manacles requires three successes at DC 22, average manacles require four successes at DC&nbsp;27, good manacles require five successes at DC 32, and superior manacles require six successes at DC 42.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=32'),
('MANACLES_SUPERIOR)', 'equipment', 'Manacles (Superior)', '17', NULL, '5000', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can manacle someone who is willing or otherwise at your mercy as an exploration activity taking 10–30 seconds depending on the creature’s size and how many manacles you apply. A two-legged creature with its legs bound takes a –15-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds, and a two-handed creature with its wrists bound has to succeed at a DC 5 flat check any time it uses a manipulate action or else that action fails. This DC may be higher depending on how tightly the manacles constrain the hands. A creature bound to a stationary object is immobilized. For creatures with more or fewer limbs, the GM determines what effect manacles have, if any. Freeing a creature from poor manacles requires two successful DC 17 Thievery checks, simple manacles requires three successes at DC 22, average manacles require four successes at DC&nbsp;27, good manacles require five successes at DC 32, and superior manacles require six successes at DC 42.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=32'),
('MATERIAL_COMPONENT_POUCH', 'equipment', 'Material Component Pouch', '0', NULL, '0.5', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This pouch contains material components for those spells that require them. Though the components are used up over time, you can refill spent components during your daily preparations.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=33'),
('MERCHANT_S_SCALE', 'equipment', 'Merchant''s Scale', '0', NULL, '0.2', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=34'),
('MIRROR', 'equipment', 'Mirror', '0', NULL, '1.0', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=35'),
('MUG', 'equipment', 'Mug', '0', NULL, '0.01', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=36'),
('MUSICAL_INSTRUMENT_HANDHELD)', 'equipment', 'Musical Instrument (Handheld)', '0', NULL, '0.8', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Handheld instruments include bagpipes, a small set of chimes, small drums, fiddles and viols, flutes and recorders, small harps, lutes, trumpets, and similarly sized instruments. The GM might rule that an especially large handheld instrument (like a tuba) has greater Bulk. Heavy instruments such as large drums, a full set of chimes, and keyboard instruments are less portable and generally need to be stationary while played.<br><br> A virtuoso instrument gives a +1 item bonus to Performance checks using that instrument. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=37'),
('MUSICAL_INSTRUMENT_HEAVY)', 'equipment', 'Musical Instrument (Heavy)', '0', NULL, '2.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Handheld instruments include bagpipes, a small set of chimes, small drums, fiddles and viols, flutes and recorders, small harps, lutes, trumpets, and similarly sized instruments. The GM might rule that an especially large handheld instrument (like a tuba) has greater Bulk. Heavy instruments such as large drums, a full set of chimes, and keyboard instruments are less portable and generally need to be stationary while played.<br><br> A virtuoso instrument gives a +1 item bonus to Performance checks using that instrument. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=37'),
('MUSICAL_INSTRUMENT_VIRTUOSO_HANDHELD)', 'equipment', 'Musical Instrument (Virtuoso Handheld)', '3', NULL, '50.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Handheld instruments include bagpipes, a small set of chimes, small drums, fiddles and viols, flutes and recorders, small harps, lutes, trumpets, and similarly sized instruments. The GM might rule that an especially large handheld instrument (like a tuba) has greater Bulk. Heavy instruments such as large drums, a full set of chimes, and keyboard instruments are less portable and generally need to be stationary while played.<br><br> A virtuoso instrument gives a +1 item bonus to Performance checks using that instrument. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=37'),
('MUSICAL_INSTRUMENT_VIRTUOSO_HEAVY)', 'equipment', 'Musical Instrument (Virtuoso Heavy)', '3', NULL, '100.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Handheld instruments include bagpipes, a small set of chimes, small drums, fiddles and viols, flutes and recorders, small harps, lutes, trumpets, and similarly sized instruments. The GM might rule that an especially large handheld instrument (like a tuba) has greater Bulk. Heavy instruments such as large drums, a full set of chimes, and keyboard instruments are less portable and generally need to be stationary while played.<br><br> A virtuoso instrument gives a +1 item bonus to Performance checks using that instrument. ', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=37'),
('OIL', 'equipment', 'Oil', '0', NULL, '0.01', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You can use oil to fuel lanterns, but you can also set a pint of oil aflame and throw it. You must first spend an Interact action preparing the oil, then throw it with another action as a ranged attack. If you hit, it splatters on the creature or in a single 5-foot square you target. You must succeed at a DC 10 flat check for the oil to ignite successfully when it hits. If the oil ignites, the target takes 1d6 fire damage.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=38'),
('PITON', 'equipment', 'Piton', '0', NULL, '0.01', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'These small spikes can be used as anchors to make climbing easier. To affix a piton, you must hold it in one hand and use a hammer to drive it in with your other hand. You can attach a rope to the hammered piton so that you don’t fall all the way to the ground on a critical failure while Climbing.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=39'),
('RATIONS', 'equipment', 'Rations', '0', NULL, '0.4', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rations for 1 week', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=40'),
('RELIGIOUS_SYMBOL_SILVER)', 'equipment', 'Religious Symbol (Silver)', '0', NULL, '2.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This piece of wood or silver is emblazoned with an image representing a deity. Some divine spellcasters, such as clerics, can use a religious symbol of their deity as a divine focus to use certain abilities and cast some spells. A religious symbol must be held in one hand to use it.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=41'),
('RELIGIOUS_SYMBOL_WOODEN)', 'equipment', 'Religious Symbol (Wooden)', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This piece of wood or silver is emblazoned with an image representing a deity. Some divine spellcasters, such as clerics, can use a religious symbol of their deity as a divine focus to use certain abilities and cast some spells. A religious symbol must be held in one hand to use it.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=41'),
('RELIGIOUS_TEXT', 'equipment', 'Religious Text', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This manuscript contains scripture of a particular religion. Some divine spellcasters, such as clerics, can use a religious text as a divine focus to use certain abilities and cast some spells. A religious text must be held in one hand to use it.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=42'),
('REPAIR_KIT', 'equipment', 'Repair Kit', '0', NULL, '2.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A repair kit allows you to perform simple repairs while traveling. It contains a portable anvil, tongs, woodworking tools, a whetstone, and oils for conditioning leather and wood. You can use a repair kit to Repair items using the Crafting skill. A superb repair kit gives you a +1&nbsp;item bonus to the check.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=43'),
('REPAIR_KIT_SUPERB)', 'equipment', 'Repair Kit (Superb)', '3', NULL, '25.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A repair kit allows you to perform simple repairs while traveling. It contains a portable anvil, tongs, woodworking tools, a whetstone, and oils for conditioning leather and wood. You can use a repair kit to Repair items using the Crafting skill. A superb repair kit gives you a +1&nbsp;item bonus to the check.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=43'),
('ROPE', 'equipment', 'Rope', '0', NULL, '0.5', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=44'),
('SACK', 'equipment', 'Sack', '0', NULL, '0.01', NULL, 'L', '8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A sack can hold up to 8 Bulk worth of items. A sack containing 2 Bulk or less can be worn on the body, usually tucked into a belt. You can carry a sack with one hand, but must use two hands to transfer items in and out.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=45'),
('SADDLEBAGS', 'equipment', 'Saddlebags', '0', NULL, '0.2', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Saddlebags come in a pair. Each can hold up to 3 Bulk of items. The Bulk value given is for saddlebags worn by a mount. If you are carrying or stowing saddlebags, they count as 1 Bulk instead of light Bulk.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=46'),
('SATCHEL', 'equipment', 'Satchel', '0', NULL, '0.1', '2', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A satchel can hold up to 2 Bulk worth of items. If you are carrying or stowing a satchel rather than wearing it over your shoulder, it counts as light Bulk instead of negligible.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=47'),
('SCHOLARLY_JOURNAL', 'equipment', 'Scholarly Journal', '3', NULL, '6.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Scholarly journals are uncommon. Each scholarly journal is a folio on a very specific topic, such as vampires or the history of a single town or neighborhood of a city. If you spend 1 minute referencing an academic journal before attempting a skill check to Recall Knowledge about the subject, you gain a +1 item bonus to the check. A compendium of journals costs five times as much as a single journal and requires both hands to use; each compendium contains several journals and grants its bonus on a broader topic, such as all undead or a whole city. The GM determines what scholarly journals are available in any location.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=64'),
('SCHOLARLY_JOURNAL_COMPENDIUM)', 'equipment', 'Scholarly Journal (Compendium)', '3', NULL, '30.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Scholarly journals are uncommon. Each scholarly journal is a folio on a very specific topic, such as vampires or the history of a single town or neighborhood of a city. If you spend 1 minute referencing an academic journal before attempting a skill check to Recall Knowledge about the subject, you gain a +1 item bonus to the check. A compendium of journals costs five times as much as a single journal and requires both hands to use; each compendium contains several journals and grants its bonus on a broader topic, such as all undead or a whole city. The GM determines what scholarly journals are available in any location.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=64'),
('SCROLL_CASE', 'equipment', 'Scroll Case', '0', NULL, '0.1', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Scrolls, maps, and other rolled documents are stored in scroll cases for safe transport.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=48'),
('SHEATH', 'equipment', 'Sheath', '0', NULL, '0.01', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A sheath or scabbard lets you easily carry a weapon on your person.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=49'),
('SIGNAL_WHISTLE', 'equipment', 'Signal Whistle', '0', NULL, '0.08', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When sounded, a signal whistle can be heard clearly up to half a mile away across open terrain.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=50'),
('SLING_BULLETS', 'equipment', 'Sling Bullets', '0', NULL, '0.01', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, '10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Weapons.aspx'),
('SNARE_KIT', 'equipment', 'Snare Kit', '0', NULL, '5.0', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit contains tools and materials for creating snares. A snare kit allows you to Craft snares using the Crafting skill. A specialist snare kit gives you a +1 item bonus to the check.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=51'),
('SNARE_KIT_SPECIALIST)', 'equipment', 'Snare Kit (Specialist)', '3', NULL, '55.0', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This kit contains tools and materials for creating snares. A snare kit allows you to Craft snares using the Crafting skill. A specialist snare kit gives you a +1 item bonus to the check.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=51'),
('SOAP', 'equipment', 'Soap', '0', NULL, '0.02', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=52'),
('SPELLBOOK_BLANK)', 'equipment', 'Spellbook (Blank)', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A spellbook holds the written knowledge necessary to learn and prepare various spells, a necessity for wizards (who typically get one for free) and a useful luxury for other spellcasters looking to learn additional spells. Each spellbook can hold up to 100 spells. The Price listed is for a blank spellbook.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=53'),
('SPYGLASS', 'equipment', 'Spyglass', '0', NULL, '20.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A typical spyglass lets you see eight times farther than normal. A fine spyglass adds a +1 item bonus to Perception checks to notice details at a distance.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=54'),
('SPYGLASS_FINE)', 'equipment', 'Spyglass (Fine)', '4', NULL, '80.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A typical spyglass lets you see eight times farther than normal. A fine spyglass adds a +1 item bonus to Perception checks to notice details at a distance.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=54'),
('SURVEY_MAP', 'equipment', 'Survey Map', '3', NULL, '10.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Maps are uncommon. Most maps you can find are simple and functional. A survey map details a single location in excellent detail. One of these maps gives you a +1 item bonus to Survival checks and any skill checks to Recall Knowledge, provided the checks are related to the location detailed on the map. Maps sometimes come in atlases, containing a number of maps of the same quality, often on similar topics. An atlas costs five times as much as a single map and requires both hands to use. The GM determines what maps are available in any location.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=65'),
('SURVEY_MAP_ATLAS)', 'equipment', 'Survey Map (Atlas)', '3', NULL, '50.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Maps are uncommon. Most maps you can find are simple and functional. A survey map details a single location in excellent detail. One of these maps gives you a +1 item bonus to Survival checks and any skill checks to Recall Knowledge, provided the checks are related to the location detailed on the map. Maps sometimes come in atlases, containing a number of maps of the same quality, often on similar topics. An atlas costs five times as much as a single map and requires both hands to use. The GM determines what maps are available in any location.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=65'),
('TACK', 'equipment', 'Tack', '0', NULL, '4.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Tack includes all the gear required to outfit a riding animal, including a saddle, bit and bridle, and stirrups if necessary. Especially large or oddly shaped animals might require specialty saddles. These can be more expensive or hard to find, as determined by the GM. The Bulk value given is for tack worn by a creature. If carried, the Bulk increases to 2.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=55'),
('TEN_FOOT_POLE', 'equipment', 'Ten-Foot Pole', '0', NULL, '0.01', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When wielding this long pole, you can use Seek to search a square up to 10 feet away. The pole is not sturdy enough to use as a weapon.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=56'),
('TENT_FOUR_PERSON)', 'equipment', 'Tent (Four-Person)', '0', NULL, '5.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=57'),
('TENT_PAVILION)', 'equipment', 'Tent (Pavilion)', '2', NULL, '40.0', NULL, '12', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=57'),
('TENT_PUP)', 'equipment', 'Tent (Pup)', '0', NULL, '0.8', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'No description', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=57'),
('THIEVES_TOOLS', 'equipment', 'Thieves'' Tools', '0', NULL, '3.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need thieves’ tools to Pick Locks or Disable Devices (of some types) using the Thievery skill. Infiltrator thieves’ tools add a +1 item bonus to checks to Pick Locks and Disable Devices. If your thieves’ tools are broken, you can repair them by replacing the lock picks with replacement picks appropriate to your tools; this doesn’t require using the Repair action.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=58'),
('THIEVE_S_TOOLS_INFILTRATOR_PICKS)', 'equipment', 'Thieve''s Tools (Infiltrator Picks)', '3', NULL, '3.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need thieves’ tools to Pick Locks or Disable Devices (of some types) using the Thievery skill. Infiltrator thieves’ tools add a +1 item bonus to checks to Pick Locks and Disable Devices. If your thieves’ tools are broken, you can repair them by replacing the lock picks with replacement picks appropriate to your tools; this doesn’t require using the Repair action.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=58'),
('THIEVE_S_TOOLS_INFILTRATOR)', 'equipment', 'Thieve''s Tools (Infiltrator)', '3', NULL, '50.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need thieves’ tools to Pick Locks or Disable Devices (of some types) using the Thievery skill. Infiltrator thieves’ tools add a +1 item bonus to checks to Pick Locks and Disable Devices. If your thieves’ tools are broken, you can repair them by replacing the lock picks with replacement picks appropriate to your tools; this doesn’t require using the Repair action.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=58'),
('THIEVES_TOOLS_REPLACEMENT_PICKS)', 'equipment', 'Thieves'' Tools (Replacement Picks)', '0', NULL, '0.3', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'You need thieves’ tools to Pick Locks or Disable Devices (of some types) using the Thievery skill. Infiltrator thieves’ tools add a +1 item bonus to checks to Pick Locks and Disable Devices. If your thieves’ tools are broken, you can repair them by replacing the lock picks with replacement picks appropriate to your tools; this doesn’t require using the Repair action.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=58'),
('TOOL_LONG)', 'equipment', 'Tool (Long)', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This entry is a catchall for basic hand tools that don’t have a specific adventuring purpose. A hoe, shovel, or sledgehammer is a long tool, and a hand drill, ice hook, or trowel is a short tool. A tool can usually be used as an improvised weapon, dealing 1d4 damage for a short tool or 1d6 for a long tool. The GM determines the damage type that’s appropriate or adjusts the damage if needed.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=59'),
('TOOL_SHORT)', 'equipment', 'Tool (Short)', '0', NULL, '0.4', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This entry is a catchall for basic hand tools that don’t have a specific adventuring purpose. A hoe, shovel, or sledgehammer is a long tool, and a hand drill, ice hook, or trowel is a short tool. A tool can usually be used as an improvised weapon, dealing 1d4 damage for a short tool or 1d6 for a long tool. The GM determines the damage type that’s appropriate or adjusts the damage if needed.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=59'),
('TORCH', 'equipment', 'Torch', '0', NULL, '0.01', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A torch sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius (and dim light to the next 20 feet). It can be used as an improvised weapon that deals 1d4 bludgeoning damage plus 1 fire damage.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=60'),
('VIAL', 'equipment', 'Vial', '0', NULL, '0.05', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'A simple glass vial holds up to 1 ounce of liquid.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=61'),
('WATERSKIN', 'equipment', 'Waterskin', '0', NULL, '0.05', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'When it’s full, a waterskin has roughly 1 day’s worth of water for a Small or Medium creature.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=62'),
('WRITING_SET', 'equipment', 'Writing Set', '0', NULL, '1.0', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Using a writing set, you can draft correspondence and scribe scrolls. A set includes stationery, including a variety of paper and parchment, as well as ink, a quill or inkpen, sealing wax, and a simple seal. If you’ve written a large amount, you can refill your kit with extra ink and paper.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=63'),
('WRITING_SET_EXTRA_INK_AND_PAPER)', 'equipment', 'Writing Set (Extra Ink and Paper)', '0', NULL, '0.1', NULL, 'L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Using a writing set, you can draft correspondence and scribe scrolls. A set includes stationery, including a variety of paper and parchment, as well as ink, a quill or inkpen, sealing wax, and a simple seal. If you’ve written a large amount, you can refill your kit with extra ink and paper.', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Equipment.aspx?ID=63'),
('KIT_ALCHEMIST', 'equipment', 'Kit, Alchemist', '0', NULL, '9.6', NULL, '4.6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'If you want to quickly decide how to spend your starting money on what your class needs, start with one of these kits. Note than an adventurer’s pack, which is included in each kit, contains a backpack, a bedroll, two belt pouches, 10 pieces of chalk, flint and steel, 50 feet of rope, 2 weeks’ rations, soap, 5 torches, and a waterskin.<br>Armor studded leather armor<br>Weapons 20 sling bullets, dagger, sling<br>Gear 2 sets of caltrops, adventurer''s pack, alchemist''s tools, bandolier, basic crafter''s book, sheath', NULL, 'https://2e.aonprd.com/Rules.aspx?ID=240'),
